title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Dissolve yeast with sugar in milk.
Cut shortening with flour.
Add milk to flour.
Mix; knead.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake until brown in a 450° oven.
Sweet milk may be used instead of buttermilk.

title: italian garden soup
directions: In a large pot over medium heat, combine oil, onions, celery, red pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until onions are slightly soft.
Add stock, beans, carrots, bay leaves, basil, marjoram, oregano, thyme and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add squash and tomatoes and simmer 5 to 7 minutes longer or until carrots and squash are just tender. Discard bay leaves.
Serves 24.
Keeps refrigerated 3 to 4 days.

title: kapusta
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Put sauerkraut into frypan.
Dice apple and onion and add to sauerkraut. Bring to a simmer for 1 hour, adding water as it simmers.
At this point, add the fried bacon, bacon grease and brown sugar.
Simmer 1 hour. Always add water right from the start, and as you go along.
This is important so that the Kapusta won't stick to bottom of pan and burn. Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine milk, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well; set aside.
Alternately layer onions, broccoli and cheese in pie shells.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Place pies on cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Add cherry pie filling and return to boil.
Remove from heat and add cherry jello, pineapple, lemon juice and Coke.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts if desired.
Cool.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together real good in extra large bowl.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons mix to each cup hot water. Very good.
Full bodied taste.
Makes enough to share with your friends!

title: summer vegetable casserole
directions: Cook onion and zucchini until almost tender.
Combine with soup, sour cream and carrots.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Grease a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Place half the stuffing in bottom of pan and top with vegetable mixture, then with remaining stuffing.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tom's green chili spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously butter loaf pan.
Combine 2/3 cup milk with the eggs; beat well and set aside.
In medium saucepan over low heat, combine remaining milk with the butter; bring just to a simmer.
Increase heat slightly; add the cornmeal in a steady stream, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt.
Remove from heat; pour in egg mixture.
Whisk until smooth.
Add chilies; whisk to combine.
Sprinkle baking powder over all; continue whisking to combine.
Pour batter into dish; bake until puffy and golden, about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Place fish in shallow dish.
Combine oil, parsley, lemon juice, onion, mustard, salt and dash of pepper. Pour over fish.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours, turning occasionally, or marinate in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours. Drain, reserving marinade.
Place fish in well-greased wire broiler.
Grill over medium-hot coals until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup pecans.
Shape into 2 large balls and roll in 1 cup pecans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake another 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Mix chicken with mushroom soup, celery soup, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with onion, potatoes, carrots and peas.

title: cherry meringue dessert
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Blend shortening with sugar, creaming well. Blend in egg yolks and milk; beat well. Add the dry ingredients all at once; stir until mixture forms a dough.
Press into bottom of well-greased 9-inch round layer pan.
Chop pecans; reserve 2 Tbsp. for Meringue. Sprinkle remainder over dough. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

Cool. Heat pie filling and add almond extract. Cool. Transfer the cookie circle to baking sheet. Beat egg whites until soft mounds form. Add 1/4 c. sugar gradually, beating well after each addition. Beat until meringue stands in stiff straight peaks.
Drop meringue by tablespoonfuls around edge on top of circle. Sprinkle with reserved pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Fill center with cherry filling.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, break 1/2 of angel food cake in bite size pieces.
Beat egg yolks and butter until creamy.
Add powdered sugar; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 on cake pieces. Top with 1/2 of candy bars.
Repeat the 3 layers.
Chill.

title: rosettes(serves 36)
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Get oil hot.
Put iron in bowl and into hot oil until golden brown.
Remove and dust with powdered sugar.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes crosswise in 3/8-inch thick slices.
In small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper until frothy.
In separate small bowls, place bread crumbs and flour.

title: egyptian rice and lentils(healthy recipe)
directions: Soak lentils in some hot water for 1 hour.
Drain and place in a saucepan; cover with water by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil; add 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Saute chopped onion in 1 tablespoon of olive oil until golden.
Add cumin, cinnamon and rice.
Stir to coat with oil. Add water and lentils with their liquid, 1/4 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Stir; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook 25 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.

title: kentucky hot paws(yields 60 servings)
directions: In heavy saucepan, blend flour into butter until smooth.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, over moderate heat until thickened.
Stir in cheese with a whisk.
Take 1 cup of sauce and blend into beaten eggs, then add to remaining sauce, stirring constantly for about 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Arrange toasted bread on pan.
Top each bread slice with slice of turkey and 1/2 cup of sauce.
Garnish with grated cheese, if desired, and a slice of crisp bacon or bacon chips.
Cook 1 minute in moderate oven.

title: guacamole (avocado sauce)
directions: Peel and mash avocado flesh.
Mix with all other ingredients and pile into serving dish.
If you are not serving immediately, cover with foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Serve as dip with tortilla chips or use as a sauce or salad.

title: chocolate pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Mix together flour and baking soda in small bowl.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips and vanilla until mixture is smooth. Transfer mixture to bowl.
Cool completely.
Stir in eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Add remaining chips and nuts.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (30 to 35 minutes).
Test for them to be done. Cool 2 to 3 minutes before handling.

title: hawaii bread dip
directions: Squeeze all water out of spinach (do not cook).
Add to other ingredients; let set 8 hours, if possible.
Use with Hawaiian bread or other chips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef.
While beef is browning, cook carrots, corn and beans.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes; drain.
Drain oil from beef.
In a bowl mix beef and vegetables.
Pour into a deep pie pan.
Spread the mashed potatoes on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until the potatoes are slightly brown.

title: french bread
directions: Combine lukewarm water and yeast.
Mix hot water, salt, sugar and shortening.
After cool, add yeast mixture.
Add 8 cups flour. Stir until mixed.
Let stand 10 minutes; stir again.
Repeat 4 times.
Separate into 4 equal parts.
Let rest again for 10 minutes. On floured board, take one part and make rectangle, then roll and press edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with rest of dough.
Place 2 rolls per sheet.
Score top 4 or 5 times. Cover with cloth and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
After removing from oven, take oleo or butter and grease top of loaves.
This recipe has been doubled because I make 4 loaves at a time and store loaves in the freezer.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Add in sour cream and frosting.
Mix well and spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over top.
Bake approximately 42 to 52 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Marinate venison overnight in vinegar, salt and 2 cloves of garlic; cover with cold water.
Place venison in crock-pot after draining liquid.
Add chopped garlic, onion, brown sugar, salt and pepper to taste, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar and tomatoes.
Cook on high until tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: crescent roll and vegetables
directions: Press rolls in the bottom of a cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Mix together mayo, cream cheese and dressing.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Shave carrots, broccoli and cauliflower and sprinkle on top.
Makes 2 cookie sheets.
Do not prepare ahead of time.

title: spanikopitas
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
On a floured board, roll each sheet to a 12-inch square, then cut into 16 (3-inch) squares.
Combine spinach, eggs, cheese, onion and parsley.
Spoon mixture in center of squares.
Brush egg wash around edges of pastry.
Fold pastry over filling to form triangle; seal edges.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and brush tops with egg wash.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 32 triangles.

title: betty's brownies
directions: Mix together and bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well, then add oats and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels.
Melt oleo.
Add the 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together in pan.
Pat into a crust.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: mexican eggplant
directions: Saute ground beef and onion together to brown beef, then add the next 5 ingredients.
Simmer very gently for 15 to 20 minutes. Lay sliced eggplant on top.
Cook for a few more minutes until eggplant is tender.
Sprinkle eggplant with cheese.
Cover and let steam to melt cheese.
Serve with steamed rice.
Delicious.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown sausage or beef with onions; drain off fat.
Stir in chilies and spices.
Prepare baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix milk and flour until smooth; add eggs and beat well. Combine remaining ingredients with meat mixture.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with taco sauce or salsa sauce.

title: rolls
directions: Bring to a boil the vanilla pudding and milk.
Remove from stove.
Add oleo and salt.
Let cool.
Add 3 beaten eggs.
Mix together 1 cup flour and yeast; add to other mixture and let set for 30 minutes.
Add 6 cups flour; let raise.
Knead and let rise. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350°.

title: bacon cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce; use cauliflower and broccoli flowerets and onion; top with bacon.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Seal with Miracle Whip, then sugar; spread evenly over Miracle Whip.
Seal and set overnight.
Toss right before serving; mix well, then add Cheddar cheese and stir in lightly.

title: chocolate orange granola cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, allspice and salt.
Set aside.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread evenly on cooled crust.
Be careful to cover crust well.
Refrigerate.
Dissolve jello with 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes to jell.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: potato soup
directions: In a medium size pot or slow cooker, place 2 1/2 cups water, salt, pepper, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cook until tender. Make a paste with 2 tablespoons flour and small amount of milk. Have this in a medium bowl.
Add about 1 cup of milk to paste and add some hot liquid from pot to this mixture, stirring all the time.
When paste mixture is warm, add to pot and stir until well mixed.
Leave on low heat until thickened.
Stir every once in a while to keep from sticking.
Very good on a cold day with cornbread and a grilled cheese sandwich!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot.
Remove from heat.
Mix all other ingredients in pot with margarine.
Work with both hands until mixed good.
Make balls to suit yourself.
Lay out on wax paper.
When you have finished this, melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler. Roll balls into this and lay out on wax paper. Put in a cool place.
May need to keep heating chocolate.

title: nutty balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Chill.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: almond roca
directions: Grate chocolate and set aside.
Chop almonds.
Line cookie sheet (10 x 13-inch) with foil.
Spread layer of almonds on bottom.
Put layer of chocolate over (1/2 of each).
Combine sugar and butter; cook and stir until it reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and pour over pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate and almonds over. Let cool, then break.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Place in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Dot with butter and bake desired amount at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolls for 1 or 2
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix all of the ingredients together and fill pan about 3/4 full.
Bake in a 400° or 425° oven until brown. Makes 6 to 8.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to tomato mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: snowball doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot pot of oil.
Turn when lightly browned.
Roll in 10x sugar if desired.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer on shredded lettuce, onions, tomatoes, black olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chip.

title: quick and easy pizza bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven according to directions on pizza crust container. Roll pizza crust dough out flat.
Cut one-inch wide diagonal strips across the dough.
Place on greased pizza pan.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Mozzarella cheese over dough strips.
Place in oven and bake according to pizza crust instructions, about 7 to 10 minutes or until bread strips begin to brown.
Remove from oven.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into patties.
Fry until brown. Serves 4 people.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients; add dates and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured large baking pan.
Dissolve brown sugar in hot water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.
Pudding is delicious with whipped topping.

title: rich chilled banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, water and pudding powder with a mixer. Chill pudding 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. In a large bowl, layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding; repeat. End with wafers. Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover baking pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Beat egg yolks, brown sugar and oil together.
Combine remaining ingredients at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool and fill with frosting.

title: dumplings for stew
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Roll 1/2 inch thick. Cut into small squares.
Drop into hot broth; cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar; cool slightly.
Beat eggs in small bowl with whisk and add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour until thoroughly blended. Add pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut before completely cool.
Makes 24 to 30 pieces.

title: fumi salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seeds in pan with a little butter. Mix cabbage and onions in a large bowl. Just before adding dressing, add nuts, seeds and crushed Top Ramen noodles.

title: bandito buffalo wings
directions: Place seasoning mix in heavy plastic food storage bag.
Add a few chicken wings and shake until well coated.
Repeat to coat all pieces.
Place in lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear. Serve hot with salsa for dipping.
Makes 2 dozen appetizers.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Let boil 5 minutes, then partially cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake until sides leave pan.
Don't overbake.
Makes a large cake.
Add frosting.

title: cheese roll
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Form into rolls and roll tightly in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
Slice and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and dice chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place in greased baking dish.
Stir cream of chicken and cream of celery together, then pour on top of diced chicken.
Salt on taste. Prepare Stove Top stuffing, using directions on box.
Spoon on top of chicken and cream and chicken and celery soup.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: old fashioned lemon sauce
directions: Combine butter, sugar, water, egg, lemon juice and rind in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil.
Amount:
1 1/3 cups of sauce.
Very good over bread pudding.

title: strawberry pecan dip
directions: In small bowl beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sushi
directions: Mix apple cider vinegar with sugar and water.
Add to rice, toss to mix and coat well.
Shape into bite size rectangles or triangles; dust with toasted sesame seed (good source of Vitamin A).
Mix in leftover bits of fresh/cooked vegetables, meats; mix into rice.
Healthy, filling.
Sushi is vinegared rice.
Sashimi is raw fish..sometimes used to top sushi.

title: crusty beef casserole
directions: In skillet:
Brown hamburger with onion and garlic (to taste). Add tomato sauce and chili powder (to taste).

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in remainder of ingredients. Chill 24 hours for flavors to blend.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in ungreased 3-quart casserole dish. Cover with the crushed cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and place in casserole dish.
Add wine, seasoning salt, Worcestershire sauce and margarine (more if needed).
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage, peppers and almonds, drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake 20 - 30 minutes or slow cook longer.

title: dressing
directions: Pour dressing over vegetables 10 to 15 minutes before serving and toss.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream together shortening, sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then add 2 (1 ounce) squares of chocolate.

title: tomato pickles
directions: Cook all ingredients 5 minutes and pour in jars and seal.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside. Beat egg yolks until lemony.
Beat in bowl and add sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; arrange in a baking dish with lid.
Put onion over pork chops; pour sauce over the top.
Bake, covered, in a moderately slow oven (300° to 325°) for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugars and milk.
Bring to a boil in saucepan, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Boil slowly until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Add nuts.
Beat until thick and glossy.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or foil.

title: dutch meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix all items and form into a loaf.
Microwave on 70% power for 30 minutes or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Put in pot; salt and pepper on top.
Add chili powder over top of everything.
Add 1/2 can of water, if necessary.
Cook 1 hour.

title: spicy sherried walnuts
directions: Add all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add walnut halves, stir until coated.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Dry on cookie sheet.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine chocolate morsels and half and half.
Cook over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm.
Good on ice cream or cheesecake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add beans, corn and chilies.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 30 minutes in a big pot.

title: benedictine spread
directions: Blend grated cucumber and onion juice into cream cheese.
Beat until consistency desired.
Add food coloring to create a pale green tint and blend.
This is a light and tasty spread for sandwiches or use as a dip with crackers and chips.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato salad
directions: Layer bacon, lettuce, tomatoes, broccoli and onion in order listed in a large glass salad bowl.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread sour cream in the bottom of a dish.
Pour sauce over sour cream and spread evenly.
Place tiny shrimp on top.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Spread biscuits in muffin tin.
Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Mix with pizza sauce and put in muffin tin.
Sprinkle cheese and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 10.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with electric beater.
Put all other ingredients in, mixing well by hand.
Coat pie plate with oil or butter.
Cook about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: one dish dinner
directions: In shallow casserole dish, mix oil with first 3 ingredients. Add potatoes and onion, turning to coat all sides.
Cook, covered, on high (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes until tender; push potatoes towards edge of casserole dish.
Cut each zucchini lengthwise into 2 pieces.
Add zucchini pieces and peppers to casserole. Cook, covered, for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Melt cheese on top, 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: garden fresh tastin corn anytime
directions: Add corn to oil (not too hot). Fry slowly, stirring often. When corn begins to soften and thicken naturally, add flour, stirring to blend evenly. Add milk, cooking slowly, until creamy, but not too thick. Add salt last or else corn will toughen.

title: cassie's chicken pot pie "quick 'n easy"
directions: Mix all canned ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Top with remaining pie crust.
Bake until crust is golden brown at 375°. Let set about 15 minutes before serving.

title: simple pumpkin bread
directions: Stain all liquid from pumpkin.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In saucepan melt butter or oleo and gradually add and blend in flour.
Add milk gradually and then add cubed cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Saute onion, garlic and ginger in margarine.
Blend in curry powder, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in evaporated milk and coconut milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add shrimp and heat.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish; add the cubed bread.
Beat the eggs and add sugar, salt, flour and pineapple; pour over the bread. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tapioca
directions: Cook tapioca and water
until
clear.
Can
be put in a roaster and made in
oven too.
Stir occasionally.
Add Danish Dessert and sugar.
Add fruit if you wish.
Cold pack for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mister hot dish
directions: Place raw hamburger in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine celery, onion, butter and water in pan and cook until celery is tender. Add croutons and toss until moistened.
Spread over hamburger.
Pour soup over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let set 15 minutes, cutting into squares.

title: hacienda
directions: Brown sausage, onion, and bell peppers together in a skillet. Drain. Mix in tomatoes and macaroni and cheese. Stir together. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Add cheese to margarine.
Let set until they are at room temperature.
Then beat with mixer until blended.
Add flour, pepper and Tabasco (you can not use a mixer after you add flour). Stir in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten a little with thumb.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Check often as they can burn easily.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper, onions, eggs and crackers.
Mash into pan like a meat loaf.
Add cheese over meat.
Add mashed potatoes and butter over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Add layer of cheese over potatoes. Bake additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: savory sausage coffee cake
directions: Saute onions and sausage until brown and crumbly.
Drain fat off.
Add cheeses, egg, Tabasco sauce, salt and parsley.
Combine the biscuit mix, milk and mayonnaise.
Place half of biscuit batter in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour sausage mixture over batter.
Mix egg yolk with water; brush on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool 5 to 8 minutes before cutting. Serves 6 for breakfast or brunch.

title: easy parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Put chopped rhubarb in bottom of pan. Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb. Then sprinkle strawberry or raspberry jello over rhubarb. Then sprinkle cake mix over this. Carefully pour cold water over all.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper, then add to the skillet and brown. Remove the chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
In the same skillet, cook the onion and celery until tender (do not brown). Skim off excess fat and discard. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Pour the mixture over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for about 50 minutes or until the chicken is done and no pink remains, basting 2 or 3 times during baking.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Blend it all for 1 minute (or beat it hard with an eggbeater if you don't have a blender).
Pour it over the mixture in the pie plate and bake for 35 minutes at 350° if pan is metal, a bit longer if it's glass.
Let it stand 3 or 4 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually as you continue to beat the mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boil over low heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, chips, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Stir 1 or 2 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Beat in mashed bananas.
Sift the dry ingredients twice and mix into banana mixture only until flour is moist.
Do not overmix.
Add the nuts.
Bake in 2 large loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or bake in 6 small loaf pans for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Wash persimmons; put through sieve to remove seeds.
Combine persimmon pulp, eggs, sugar, milk and butter in large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Grease pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: quickie coffee cake
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together egg, yogurt, cake mix and raisins.
Spread in pan.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Delicious also when cooled.

title: bible bread
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, stir the liquid ingredients together.
Gradually add the liquid to the dry ingredients; mix the dough well.
Lightly oil and flour a cookie sheet.
Pat dough out until it is 1/2-inch thick.
(Cover your fingers with flour to keep the dough from sticking.)
Prick the dough with a fork, then bake the dough at 425° for about 10 minutes, or until it is golden brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk alternately with wafer crumbs.
Add nuts and coconut.
Blend well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: ice cream in a can
directions: Mix pudding, evaporated milk, milk, cream, sugar, vanilla and dash of salt together.
Pour equal amounts into the 4 small coffee cans.
Duct tape the lids to the cans, to make a tight seal. Place the smaller can into the larger one.
Pack the can with ice cubes.
Sprinkle a little salt on the ice.
Tape the lid on the large can.
Roll the can all around.
Check after 8 - 10 minutes to see if your ice cream is getting firm.
Continue until you have the consistency you desire.

title: western beef hash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper. Increase heat to medium-high.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in salsa.
Continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Top with mushrooms and olives.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place bread in casserole dish. Sprinkle sausage and onions on top.
Blend eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over the bread and sausage. Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until morning. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: felix's fabulous fudge(as taken from aunt geneva's foolproof fudge)
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in top of double boiler over boiling water, stirring to help the melting process.
Or follow microwave directions on chocolate morsels package.
Remove chocolate from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spread fudge evenly in 8-inch square pan which is lightly oiled.
Chill fudge 2 hours.

title: tomato rarebit on toast
directions: Combine evaporated milk, tomatoes, cheese and mustard in medium-size saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
(Do not boil.)
Beat eggs slightly in small bowl. Stir in 1/2 cup or more of hot mixture slowly.
Then stir back into remaining saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until thick.
Serve on toast.

title: mexican-style corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until well blended. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder, sugar and vanilla; add salt.
Stir in nuts and crackers.
Pour into a well-greased pie pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and add topping.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Let balls dry out slightly.

title: banana bread
directions: Add each ingredient in order listed.

title: crab on english muffin
directions: Let cheese and butter come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together; grate cheese.
Mix and spread on muffins. Cut into 4 pieces.
Place on cookie sheet under broiler until lightly browned.
May be frozen before broiling.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding sherbet last.
Serves 20.

title: ranch-style potato salad
directions: Microwave potatoes and water in covered dish on High for 14 to 16 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes. Drain.
Put cheese and dressing in microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir in potatoes. Add other ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Serve warm or refrigerated.

title: banana bread*
directions: Cream shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients, mix. Add bananas and lemon juice.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours in greased bread pan.

title: jan's chicken loaf
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Mix chicken, mushroom soup and 1 cup shredded cheese.
Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms.
Beat about 25 strokes and form dough into ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 to 10 times.
Roll dough into 14 x 11-inch rectangle and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon chicken mixture lengthwise down center of dough and fold sides over mixture.
Cut small slits in top and seal the ends together.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light brown. Mix cream of chicken soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese together and simmer.
Use as gravy over slices of chicken loaf.
Serves about 6 smaller portions or 4 "hungry man" portions.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and mix in chocolate until chocolate is completely melted.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
With a wire whip, stir the egg mix constantly while pouring in the milk to blend.
Place bread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour liquid mixture over bread.
Allow to sit for 10 minutes so bread can soak up the milk.
Place pan in larger pan or deep cookie sheet.
Add water to larger pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill well before serving.

title: lemon bars
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until creamy.
Beat in 2 cups flour until blended.
Spread mixture over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage, pepper, onion and salt.
Set 1 hour, then add remaining ingredients.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Let bread thaw, but not rise.
Cut into walnut size pieces. Melt margarine.
Add beaten egg and other ingredients.
Dip pieces of bread dough in the margarine and put in a greased loaf or Bundt pan.
Let rise before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts (remove skin, if desired).
Rub with salad dressing and then coat with crushed corn flakes.
Place close together in baking pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour (until tender) at 350°.
Prepare as many pieces as needed.

title: gumbo for beginners
directions: Heat oil in black pot.
Add flour.
Brown, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken in lemon sauce
directions: In large frying pan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute about 10 minutes or until chicken is brown and fork can be inserted with ease.
Remove chicken to a dish appropriate for broiling in oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and Karo in large skillet.
Bring to rapid boil (stirring constantly) until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat quickly and pour into buttered dish.

title: avocado salad
directions: Cut avocados in half.
Scoop out inside, leaving skin intact. Mash up the meat of avocado well.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Fill shell of avocado with mix.
Serves 6.

title: funnel cake
directions: Put 2 inches of oil in skillet; heat to 375°.
In medium bowl with whisk or fork, beat eggs, 1 tablespoon oil, sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup milk.
Gradually beat in flour until smooth.
If batter is too thick, thin with milk.
Swirl batter into hot oil, starting at center and working out to make a 6-inch spiral.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes on each side until golden brown. Drain on a cookie sheet lined with paper towels.
Keep warm in 200° oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll and crush graham crackers and mix with the butter or margarine that has been melted.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with one-half of cracker mixture.
Dissolve lemon jello in the hot water.
Cool.
Stir in the granulated sugar, vanilla and cream cheese with the jello.
Beat milk until it forms peaks.
Add jello mixture and beat again.
Pour in pan and sprinkle top with the other half of the cracker and butter mixture.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind or put through blender the cranberries and oranges. Drain and save juice.
Add pineapple, bananas, walnuts and sugar. Let mixture set while mixing jello up (use fruit juice instead of cold water).
When jello mixture starts to thicken, stir in fruit mixture.

title: margo's stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain upside-down.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together until well done.
Tear up lettuce; wash and drain.
Put in large bowl.
Chop up tomatoes and add to lettuce.
Stir drained beans into hamburger. Cook 2 minutes on High.
Cool.
Shred cheese.
Drain grease from meat mixture. Add to lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Crunch chips.
Add to bowl, then add Catalina dressing.
Mix it up.
Ready to eat.

title: mock lasagna(sour cream noodle bake)
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasonings in butter and add tomato sauce and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Cook and drain noodles.
Place in baking dish in alternate layers of noodles, cheese and sauce.
Top with grated cheese and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet, breaking meat into small pieces and stirring for about 5 minutes.
Drain grease off meat. Add corn, water, tomatoes and all seasonings and bring to a boil. Then stir in rice and boil about 2 minutes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Goes well with a salad and cornbread.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken pieces in Dutch oven; barely cover with water, add salt and simmer until meat is tender.
Remove skin and bones; set chicken meat aside, reserving the broth.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, and salt; cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut into 1-inch squares, and sprinkle with flour.
Drop into briskly boiling chicken stock.
Cover tightly and simmer gently for about 40 minutes.
Add meat and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Miracle Whip.
Now add 3 to 4 tablespoons Miracle Whip and toss together.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, corn, chilies, olives, salt and chili powder. Heat to boiling.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Prepare corn bread according to package directions and pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until corn bread is done.

title: wassail to consume(christmas)
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Take off heat.
Let sit 1 hour.
Fish all spices out, then add apple cider or apple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Heat and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix all other ingredients in the butter or margarine.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Enjoy!!

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Put soup in saucepan and heat.
While soup is heating, break bread in a large bowl with eggs, salt and pepper.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Mix well with chicken.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream cheeses and 1/2 envelope taco mix with mixer.
Spread on medium size pizza pan. (Optional:
Brown ground beef with other 1/2 envelope taco mix and spread on top of cheese layer.)
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: touch of honey bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, oat bran, yeast and salt.
Heat water, honey and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat at low speed until moistened. Increase speed to medium and beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Lightly spray bowl with nonstick spray.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface. Knead 8 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place into prepared bowl, turning once to coat surface of dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place 30 minutes or until doubled.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble Oreos.
Bring ice cream and Cool Whip to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery 7 minutes in 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In the meantime, dice water chestnuts and crumb crackers.
Mix margarine, crackers and soup.
Drain celery and mix with crackers and soup mix.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apricot almond chewies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours. Shape into 1-inch balls and serve.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.

title: spinach patties
directions: Break
eggs into large mixing bowl;
add
all
remaining ingredients.
Mix well as for meat loaf.
Shape
mixture into 4 patties, for main course; 8 smaller portions
for
an appetizer course. Saute over medium heat in skillet coated
with no stick cooking spray (Pam) until crispy and browned,
about 5 minutes. Turn
patties
and	continue to cook until browned	and
cooked through,
another
5 to 10 minutes.
Keep hot
until
ready
to serve.
These are especially good with fresh
tomato
sauce and freshly grated Parmesan cheese, a green salad and French bread. Makes 2 main course servings or 4 appetizer servings.

title: apricot cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, eggs and apricot nectar.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Blend softened cream cheese and 2 teaspoons apricot nectar together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto top of batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad pie(heritage)
directions: Cook pie cherries, pineapple, sugar and flour, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and add orange jello.
Chill.
Then add nuts, bananas and brandy flavoring.
Makes two pies.
Use regular pie crusts and top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese log
directions: Put first 6 ingredients through food chopper.
Then mix with cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Form into several small rolls, then roll in chili powder.

title: carol's toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with the bay leaf.
Cool. Grate.
Mix together the remaining ingredients. Blend into potatoes.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dot with a bit of butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until baked through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. It is good cold in a sandwich.
Can use pimento instead of red pepper.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Heat all spices, onions, water and vinegar in a pan until boiling.
Boil 1 minute and then pour over roast.
Turn to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 7 days.
Turn meat twice daily.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine fruit, marshmallows and nuts; toss lightly.
Combine cream and salad dressing; fold into fruit.
Chill and serve on bed of lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: herb french bread
directions: Slice bread, but not all the way through.
Cream together all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Spread between each slice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
May have to open foil to brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute garlic and artichokes.
Add green beans, 1/2 cup bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese to mixture until thick.
Bake in microwave about 7 minutes.

title: oatmeal and chocolate cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream Crisco, eggs and sugars; gradually add dry ingredients.
Add nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tiffany's oven potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters.
Put in bowl with oil and toss to distribute oil.
Place potatoes in 4-quart casserole dish and cover with onion soup mix.
Add soy sauce; mix around.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes a tangy side dish.

title: graham dream bars
directions: Boil together sugar, oleo, milk and egg.
Cool to lukewarm and add coconut, nuts and crumbs.
Place this mixture on a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with another layer of graham crackers and frost with a mixture of 1/2 cup oleo and 2 cups powdered sugar.

title: baked potato strips
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into thin 1/4 inch strips.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In a bowl, combine the egg whites, parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Add the potatoes; toss to coat.
Place in a single layer in a 15 X 10 X 1 inch baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, turning several times.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll into sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 2-inches apart for 6 to 8 minutes, until light brown.
Place Kiss into middle and press.
Set aside to cool or in freezer for a few minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Pour a can of peaches (or any fruit) in a long shallow casserole dish with the liquid.
Sprinkle about half of the cake mix on top of the fruit and juice.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Mix some sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over the top.
Cook for 45 minutes to an hour at
450° or until the sides and top are brown.

title: happy home
directions: Mix love and happiness.
Add faith; blend in understanding, tenderness and patience.
Add forgiveness.
Toss in laughter. Generously serve the entire family.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Mix everything else together.
Add green beans last.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure and sift together three times the flour and 3/4 cup plus two tablespoons granulated sugar.

title: fish croquettes
directions: Discard skin and brown crust from fish; flake enough to equal 1 cup.
Mix with remaining ingredients except dry bread crumbs. Form into croquettes.
Roll in dry toasted bread crumbs.
Place on foil-covered baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave over and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and blend well.
Return to oven and cook 2 to 3 minutes more or until peanuts are golden brown.
Add baking soda and vanilla and gently stir until light and foamy.

title: pudding ice-cream
directions: Mix pudding, Milnot and powdered sugar together.
Pour into your ice cream freezer and fix according to your freezer's instructions.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: pepperoni spread
directions: Grind pepperoni in food processor.
Add cream cheese and rest of ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet and 1/2 of the French vanilla ice cream.
Add ginger ale.
When ready to serve, spoon in remaining ice cream.
Yields 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: gratin of apples, sweet potatoes and onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a baking dish (a heavy enameled, cast-iron dish with a nonstick surface is ideal) with nonstick baking spray.
Layer the apples, onions and potatoes, alternating layers until all of the slices are used.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except drop biscuits.
Place in pan on stove.
Thicken with flour.
Pour into greased casserole pan. Top with drop biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian seasoning mix together.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Top with olives, pepper and cheese.
Roll tightly.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill in refrigerator.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and serve.
(Insert toothpick upright into each piece for easier serving.)

title: lattice jam topped linzer(cookie from austria)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in brown sugar and cut in butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Add egg and ground almond; mix (save 1/2 cup of mixture for lattice top).
Press mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for cookie bars or use a spring-form cake pan for a round cake.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dry hot dog.
Heat oil.
Mix flour and corn meal.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and eggs.
Stir to mix.
Dip hot dogs in batter.
Let excess batter drip off.
Fry in hot oil, turning until all sides are browned (about 6 minutes).
Drain on paper towels.
Stick wooden skewer in end of each.
Serve dipped in mustard.

title: cabbage lasagne
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage and cut out core and large ribs. Saute over medium
heat
in
hot oil until just tender.
Brown meat and onion
in
large skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and rice. Simmer 20
minutes.
In
a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, layer 1/2 of cooled cabbage, then 1/2 of remaining sauce
and
1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place biscuits in sugar mixture and shake. Put into angel food cake pan. Melt margarine; add brown sugar and nuts. Pour over biscuits; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese slowly in crock-pot.
Cook sausage and drain. Saute onions and peppers.
Combine everything in a crock-pot and cook slowly until all ingredients are melted and mixed together. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: simple-to-fix great tasting spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground chuck and drain into colander.
In same pot chuck was cooked in, saute the onions and green pepper.
While sauteing, stir in spices.
When onions are nearly cooked, add remaining ingredients and ground chuck.
Simmer for 60 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve over your favorite pasta noodles.
Should serve 4 to 6 adults.

title: petits fours - easy
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 10 x 15-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients at low speed until mixed.
Beat at highest speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely.
Freeze 1 hour.
Cut into rectangle, diamonds or circles.
Refreeze.
Ice.

title: cheese chili dip
directions: Mix cheese and chili and beef.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Serve with chips.

title: best butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with electric beater until well blended.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Press with fork tines to flatten slightly.
Bake for approximately 10 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Cook oleo, cocoa and water together until it comes to a boil; pour into your mixing bowl.
Add flour, sugar, soda, salt, eggs and sour cream.
Pour into a jelly roll pan; bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Cream the two cheeses.
Add sugar gradually.
Add yolks; beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch and flour.
Add butter; mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into buttered 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cake in oven with door closed for 2 hours to dry excess moisture from cheesecake.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in water.
Add sugar and then other ingredients.
Can make 1/2 lime and 1/2 cherry.

title: biscotti
directions: Cream the shortening with the sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Sift flour. Measure and sift again with the baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in flavoring and almonds.
Turn mixture onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth. Divide dough into thirds.

Form into 3 rolls the length of the cookie sheet and 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until rolls are firm to the touch. While still warm, cut rolls crosswise into slices 3/4-inch thick.
Lay these, cut side down, on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes longer to toast.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown and season hamburger and onions, taco seasoning, green pepper and celery.
Melt Velveeta cheese and stewed tomatoes over low heat.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Form in 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets, 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: candied kielbasi
directions: Place all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cook on high until sauce slightly boils.
Lower temperature; cook 1 hour.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Spray
9-inch
square baking pan with cooking spray. In large bowl
combine
flour,
sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt.
In
medium
bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, mix
egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Add to flour mixture; stir
until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35
minutes
or until
toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in pan on wire rack.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Yields 16 servings.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Chop onions in food processor until they are mushy.
Cook ground beef and onions in skillet until ground beef is browned. In a large pot, combine all other ingredients.
Drain fat off of ground beef and onions.
Chop ground beef and onions in food processor until the meat is very fine.
Then add it to the other ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour on low heat.
Can be divided into small freezer bags and frozen for future use.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Let set a few minutes before slicing.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crumble beef into 2 quart glass measure. Add onion and garlic; mix lightly. Place in microwave oven. Cook on high for 3 minutes. Pause, stir through several times. Cook on high for 3 minutes. Pause, stir in puree and seasoning mix. Cook on high 4 minutes. Pause, remove from oven. Layer tortillas, beef mixture, and 2 1/2 cups cheese in 2 quart round microwave casserole. Cover and place in oven. Cook on high 7 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Cut into wedges and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot overnight.
Remove from bone. Discard broth.
Add rest of ingredients and cook in crock-pot all day.

title: lemon yogurt pie
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand for 1 minute. Microwave on High for 20 seconds. Stir in sugar or substitute and lemon juice. Add yogurt and lemon peel; mix well. Fold in whipped topping; spoon into crust. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pour pie filling into dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of this.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until brown. Apple and peach pie fillings are also good with this recipe.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of baking soda.
(It will foam.)
Stir well and pour over about 2 large skillets of popcorn.
May add nuts.
Divide mixture onto cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: microwave iced tea
directions: Place
water
and
sugar
in
1/2 gallon glass pitcher. Stir well
until
sugar is dissolved.
Add tea bags.
Place in large microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Let tea stand for 1/2 hour or until
pitcher
cools down.
Remove tea bags and fill remainder of pitcher with ice.
Add lemon if desired.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Add celery, green pepper and onions to vegetables.
Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: bread dumplings(good to the last crumb)
directions: Warm butter or margarine and milk in microwave. Crumble bread in large bowl. Pour the butter/milk mixture over the bread (if bread is very moist, use less or more if it's dry). Let stand for 1 hour. Add eggs, kneading into bread mixture. Form into small, firm balls about the size of golf balls or slightly larger. Place in boiling water for 20 minutes. Serve with your favorite cut of meat and gravy. Enjoy!

title: oatmeal and raisin muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups. Beat egg.
Stir in milk, oil and raisins.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once until moistened.
Fill muffin cups.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Cut meat into slices and separate.
Heat cooking oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Carefully add potatoes; cover and cook, stirring now and then, until slightly brown.
Then stir in meat; continue cooking until thoroughly heated.
Salt and pepper to taste!
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar with pineapple.
Add cheese and put in a baking dish.
Crush crackers and add melted margarine.
Place on top of pineapple and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple.
Spread into pan evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into a layer.
Dump in cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter slices over top.
Bake at 350° for fifty minutes.
Serve warm or cold. If wanted, use ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and then add beaten egg.
Work in sifted flour with baking powder and salt.
Nutmeats may be added.

title: neapolitan spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef in olive oil in heavy kettle; add salt, pepper, garlic and onion.
Blend well.
Add tomatoes, paste, water and sugar; bring to boiling.
Add mushrooms, pepperoni, oregano, rosemary, marjoram, red pepper, cheese and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about two hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over freshly cooked spaghetti. Store and freeze leftover sauce.

title: chicken casserole no. 3
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bones.
Mix soups and sour cream together.
Add cut-up chicken.
Place in large dish. Top with pecans.
Crush crackers and add melted butter.
Add to top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Blend butter, parsley, tarragon, chives, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4-inch squares of aluminum foil; wrap and freeze until firm, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Use different kinds of fruit for dipping, especially apples and bananas.

title: low calorie baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine Equal, cornstarch and spices in a medium saucepan. Slowly stir in cider. Add canned fruit. Heat slowly to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Slice apples into 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick slices. Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour spiced fruit mixture evenly over apple slices. Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 40 minutes or until apples are fork-tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: peaches 'n cream pudding cake
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Cut peaches into bite-sized pieces.
Arrange peaches in oiled 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread pudding over peaches.
Prepare cake batter according to package directions, substituting peach juice for the water.
Spread batter over pudding and peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno okra
directions: Fry bacon crisp, set aside. Add jalapeno and onion to bacon grease, saute until tender. Add okra, tomatoes and seasonings. Cook until okra is tender. Crumble bacon over top.

title: out-of-season peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
In mixing bowl, mix sugar and Bisquick.
Add milk.
Pour mixture on top of melted margarine but do not mix.
Add peaches, juice and all.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: marshmallow eggs
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water; boil to soft ball stage. Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water in large bowl.
Beat with mixer; slowly add soft ball mixture.
Continue beating until fluffy and white (10 to 15 minutes).
Put flour in a large pan; make indentations with an egg for molds.
Make 48 to 50 indentations.
Drop marshmallow mixture in each hole.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours to set good.
Roll tops over into flour so they don't stick.
Melt chocolate and dip eggs.
Set on wax paper to cool. Can decorate tops with candies while chocolate is wet.
Let set to allow chocolate to set up.

title: hamburger meat casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add peppers and onions and cook until soft.
Add sour cream, soup and pimento.
Cook noodles by directions and drain.
Combine meat mixture and noodles.
Pour in large baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese and crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put layer of crumbs and cheese in bottom of greased casserole.
Add layer of asparagus.
Cover with nuts and then cover with soup mixture.
Continue until all ingredients are used, leaving a cheese layer on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 29 minutes.

title: rice jambalaya
directions: Fry pork sausage; drain off excess fat, leaving enough to saute pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add cooked rice and other seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Very tasty.

title: apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add fruits.
Take the pineapple juice; thicken with flour (2 tablespoons) and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook until thick, then mix with Cool Whip for a topping. Very good.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Remove.
In large bowl, beat eggs well. Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish and level off.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and let cool for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares.
Squares freeze well.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Combine lemon pepper, dill weed, garlic powder and dressing. Mix well.
Place crackers in a large, double-walled paper bag or a plastic container with a lid.
Sprinkle mixture over crackers. Pour oil over all.
Shake well.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg and dissolved soda in milk.
Sift cinnamon, ginger, cloves, nutmeg, baking powder, salt and flour.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Add floured raisins.
Batter should be stiffer than for white cake.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Let cool.
Add ripe olives, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar and 1 1/2 cups Monterey Jack.
Keep enchilada sauce medium hot.
Put 1 cup sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Slide tortilla through hot sauce.
Lay out flat.
Fill about 1/2 cup beef in middle. Roll tortilla and lay flap side down.
Lay each tortilla side by side, then pour remaining sauce over all. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake in a 350° oven for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Serve with Spanish rice and mashed pinto beans.
Garnish with sour cream (optional).

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese, cubed, and can of Ro-Tel tomatoes, cut up and heat until cheese is melted.
Great with Dorito chips.

title: casserole sauce or canned soup mix
directions: Combine the above in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup of mix and 1 1/4 cups water.
Cook until thick.
Stir all the time.
This equals 1 can of undiluted soup.
Add 1 1/4 cups water to use as soup.

title: mama's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until very tender.
Drain.
Add butter and sugar to potatoes.
Cook over medium heat 20 to 30 minutes until syrup forms and boils slowly around potatoes.
Do not cook too fast or potatoes will burn.
Remove potatoes from syrup with large spoon and arrange in casserole or 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour syrup over potatoes and top with marshmallows.
Bake at 300° until marshmallows are golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
May be refrigerated several days.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Place on paper towel and press liquid out until barely moist.
Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Cover and chill mixture several hours.
Serve with chips, crackers or raw vegetables.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine and toss all ingredients.
Stir in dressing one hour before serving.

title: zucchini beef bake
directions: Cook zucchini until
tender.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in 1/2 cup bread crumbs
and
seasoning.
In saucepan, melt butter. Add flour and 1/2 teaspoon
salt; add milk.
Cook until bubbly. Add cheese until melted.
Stir in meat.
Alternate meat and zucchini.
Combine remaining bread and butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade meat sauce
directions: Melt butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Brown hamburger, onion and garlic, then drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, golden mushroom soup, bay leaf, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and sugar. Let simmer for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Place sliced mushrooms in the bottom of a casserole.
Top with chicken parts; mix water and cornstarch.
Combine with all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread into 9 x 13 dish.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Top with sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon before serving with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal brownies
directions: Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir in oats and 1 cup of the chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cheezy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, cauliflower and carrots until tender. Cook macaroni and drain well. Mix all together with ham in a casserole dish. Add salt and pepper if desired. Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted good, about 50 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Put into pie crust. Cover with remaining pie crust. Crimp edges with fork. Cut slits into the top of the crust. Brush top with egg (if desired). Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean italiano
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions and set aside. Melt butter in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring often, until tender.
Stir in rice, sour cream, cream cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: oatmeal slice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat the butter and sugars together until light.
Beat in egg and flavorings.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and ginger.
Add to butter mixture, stirring just until blended.
Batter will be stiff.
Add oats, pecans and raisins, stirring thoroughly to mix.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until set.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix well.
May be baked as a casserole.

title: creamy chicken and vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Remove chicken.
Stir in water and soup mix.
Add chicken; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Place chicken on heated platter.
Stir sour cream into sauce; heat through.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
Stir until dissolved.
Have pickles washed and sliced.
Pack cold in jars with onions on top. Fill with cold liquid, seal and store in refrigerator.
Will be ready to use in 1 week.

title: brazilian black beans
directions: Soak black beans overnight in pan full of water.
Saute onion and garlic until brown.
Put beans in and cover with water (about 6 to 7 cups).
Bring beans to a boil.
Add cilantro, cumin seed, cumin powder, tomatoes and salt.
Bring beans to a simmer.
Leave beans to simmer for 2 hours approximately.
Serve with white rice and salsa.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze excess water from spinach.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Stir again before serving.
Great with veggies.

title: chou-rouge
directions: Form hamburg and onion into a round ball; brown slowly and carefully in a Dutch oven or 10-inch skillet.
Cover and surround browned hamburg and onion mixture first with potato pieces, then with shredded cabbage.
Mix 1 can tomato soup with 1 can water; pour over cabbage.
Add a dash of red pepper, if you wish.
Simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and add applesauce.
Then stir in walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: gingerbread boys and girls
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, molasses and vinegar to a boil.
Add mixed dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Cool completely.

title: kay hill's best brownies in the world
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a glass bowl. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on Roast (Medium, 60%) for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Continue microwaving at the same speed for 2 or 3 more minutes or until melted.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine liquid ingredients, then alternate together.

title: frank and bacon twirls
directions: Slice hot dogs in half lengthwise.
Mix Cheddar, mustard, onion and Worcestershire.
Spread on cut side of hot dogs.
Fit dogs together.
Wrap with bacon slice.
Fasten with pick and grill until done.
Serve in rolls.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices bread and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and spices.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. The cheese will rise to the top during baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wesson fruit cake
directions: Boil and brush over cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix in all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole. Top with crushed crackers.
(You can use onion rings.)
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute onions in margarine until tender. Reduce heat to medium.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: beef minestrone
directions: Place the beef, 1 teaspoon salt and 4 quarts of water in a large kettle. Cover and bring to a boil. Add carrots, celery, onion, garlic, parsley and bay leaf and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.

Remove beef and carrots and set aside. Strain the broth (about 7 cups) and reserve. In kettle, combine broth, tomatoes, chickpeas, cabbage, macaroni, 2 teaspoons salt and the pepper. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 45 minutes. Slice carrots and cut meat into small pieces. Add meat to simmering soup. Add carrots when soup is done. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: banana salad
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and stir.
Add brown sugar and cold water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Take off burner.
Add vinegar, bananas and peanuts.
Layer and put in fridge.

title: chicken devine
directions: Saute vegetables, then combine all ingredients in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: low-fat cookies(from a mix)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet (or Presto cooker). Add Rice-A-Roni and saute to a light brown. Stir in hot water. Add the chicken flavor packet included in Rice-A-Roni plus the black pepper, Tabasco, onion, celery, green pepper and salt. Add chicken. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serves 10. Keeps well, is great warmed over.

title: venison on the grill
directions: Put venison pieces in Ziploc bag; pour in venison marinade. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours to tenderize. Drain and grill.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet. Add chicken and onion. Stir-fry 2 minutes. Cook noodles according to directions. Add remaining ingredients to skillet, except for noodles. Stir-fry until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are crisp-tender. Add noodles; toss to mix. Heat through. Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Arrange raspberries on bottom of crust.
Slowly pour cheese mixture over fruit.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Top cheesecake with Chocolate Glaze; chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with chips.

title: orange sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk and orange juice. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts and apricots.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream butter, vanilla pudding mix and cinnamon until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In another bowl, combine milk, undrained pineapple, coconut, raisins and vanilla.
By hand, blend milk mixture into creamed mixture.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place into larger shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water to 1-inch depth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased mold.
May add sliced eggs and sliced olives to bottom of mold.
Chill until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients to chocolate mixture and spread into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix hot water with gelatin.
Add pineapple; let thicken.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: raspberry delight
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and sugar; blend in oleo until smooth. Press into ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes; crust will not brown. Cool.

title: ham strata
directions: Cut off
crusts and cut bread in half.	Grease pan with butter and
arrange
bread
in bottom of pan.
Arrange half of ham as second
layer.
Grate cheese and sprinkle with half of combined cheeses.
Repeat
layers.
Combine	slightly
beaten eggs, seasonings	and
milk.
Pour
over	layers.
Cover	and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, make topping of crushed corn flakes and	melted	butter.
Sprinkle over Strata.	Bake 50 to 60 minutes at	375°.
Let
set for 10 minutes or longer before serving.
Use two 8 x 8-inch or one deep 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: cherry poppy seed cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In large bowl, beat powdered sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, poppy seed and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
With finger, make imprint with about 1/2 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.

title: taco chicken wings
directions: Combine flour and taco seasoning; mix in a plastic bag.
Add chicken wings, a few at a time.
Shake to coat.
Melt margarine in a pan; dip wings into melted margarine, then roll in corn chips. Return to baking pan.
