Cook in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: columbus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to the egg, then beat in the coffee and rum.
Add this to the butter and sugar mixture and continue beating until it is a soft batter.
Sift the remaining flour with the baking powder, if used, and salt and add very slowly to the batter.

Stir in the chopped nuts, adding a little extra flour if the dough is not stiff enough to roll out. Refrigerate for 1 hour, then flour a board and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into desired shapes.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 to 15 minutes until cookies are firm and pale beige.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Place sugar, butter and cream in a 4-cup glass measuring cup. Cook on 100% power for 1 minute.
Cook on 70% power for 30 seconds.
Cook on 50% power for 20 seconds.
Stir and add vanilla.

title: guacamole
directions: Note:
Choose an avocado which yields slightly to finger pressure.
Avoid those with the consistency of either a lump of granite or instant guacamole!

title: seven layer cookies(jeannemarie schwarz's favorite recipe)
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan. Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with layers of chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Let jell slightly. Mix rest of ingredients in order as listed in Jell-O.
Let refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: cranberry salad(for a large mold)
directions: Melt Jell-O and dump remaining ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate.
Stir again when begins to congeal.

title: chicken with tortillas
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Layer chicken, onions and cheese in casserole.
Spread mixed soups on the layered ingredients.
Mash tomatoes and combine with chili powder.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: popcorn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except popcorn and mayonnaise. Add just before serving.

title: chocolate and raspberry cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks, whole egg and sugar until the mixture is thick and light; fold in almonds.
Into a bowl, sift cocoa and flour together 3 times and fold into egg mixture alternately with the melted butter.

title: fish in cheese sauce
directions: Place fish in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine soup and milk.
Pour over fish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of soup mixture.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini, carrot and onion in saucepan with enough water to barely cover.
Cover and cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine undiluted chicken soup, sour cream and oregano.
Stir in vegetables.

Combine stuffing mix with butter. Spread half the stuffing mix in bottom of greased casserole; top with vegetable mix and then with remaining buttered stuffing mix. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add flavorings.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and brandy, blending after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan. Bake 70 minutes at 325°.
Allow cake to cool in pan about 30 minutes. Serves 16 to 20.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour fruit into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Crumble dry cake mix over fruit, breaking up lumps. Layer pecans over mix.
Slowly pour butter evenly over the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until the top is a golden brown.
Serve warm with or without ice cream or whipped topping.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine well. Press firmly in bottom and on sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill 1 hour before using.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs, bananas, lemon juice and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and cereal. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and syrup; add peanut butter and noodles.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: hamburger bean pot soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add to water and bring to boil; simmer for about 2 hours.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots,
potatoes, onion, bouillon, salt and pepper and simmer for 1 hour.
Brown ground beef and add.
Add rice.
Add okra.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.
May need to add water if soup is too thick.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add milk, water, egg yolks and margarine.
Mix well.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Mix with electric mixer.
Let cool; if too thick, add milk to thin.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon extract or flavor to taste.
Mix with electric mixer; let cool completely.
Pour into cooled 9-inch pastry shell.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Use 1/2 of Blue cheese with sour cream.
Blend well and add onion dip and other half of crumbled Blue cheese.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: breakfast pita pockets
directions: Crumble sausage into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until sausage is brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: willa's bean dip
directions: Mix everything together, except 1/2 cup grated cheese, sour cream and chips.
Heat in 1 quart saucepan for 5 to 7 minutes or in plastic bowl for 2 1/2 minutes in microwave and stir completely.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and baking soda; set aside. Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie, 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together and let gel.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Skim most of the fat from broth.
You should have about 1 1/2 to 2 quarts of broth.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Slow boil for 10 minutes.
Thicken broth with cornstarch that has been mixed with the cold water and slowly thicken boiling broth until it is slightly thickened.
Add the gravy browner and deboned chicken and cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice as a gumbo.
I use Minute rice.
It works fine.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix beef, egg, crumbs, onion and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs, brown in oil.
Pour off the fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and soda in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Add carrot, apples, coconut, raisins and pecans.
Stir. Make a well in center of the mixture.
Combine oil, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased or papered muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients; shape into balls, smaller for appetizers.
Bake in oven at 350° until meat is no longer pink. Broiler pan works best.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel shrimp.
Remove sand veins and wash.
Cut large shrimp in halves.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Serve in a rice ring.
Serves about 6 people.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly. Pour over spaghetti and mix well.
Put in a large bowl with a lid on it.
Refrigerate.
Can be made a couple of days before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all except chicken.
Save a little cheese and mix chopped chicken.
Put small amount of mix on tortilla, add a small amount of chopped chicken.
Roll up and put in a large baking pan.
Pour extra mix over tortilla roll-ups.
Sprinkle cheese over roll-ups. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This dish is good hot or served cold.
Cut in appetizer size pieces.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor.
Will keep in closed container in fridge for 2 weeks.

title: cheese and noodle bake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
Beat eggs well; blend in water.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until combined (dough should be pliable but not sticky).
On floured surface, knead gently 15 to 20 strokes.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
On floured surface, roll half the dough at a time to a 12-inch circle, about 1/8-inch thick.
With 3-inch round cookie cutter, cut out circles of dough.
Place one heaping teaspoon of filling on 1/2 of 1 circle.
Fold other half of circle over, making a half-moon shape.
Pinch edges together well to seal.
If necessary, crimp with fingertips again to ensure a good seal.
Place on kitchen towel or floured surface; cover while making remaining pierogi.

title: *slush
directions: In a large container, mix mashed bananas, orange juice, lemonade, sugar and water.
Divide into 3 smaller containers (13 1/2 ounce Cool Whip containers work) and freeze.
About 1 hour before serving, set out container.
Place in punch bowl or pitchers.
When ready to serve, add Wink, stirring as you pour. Punch should be slushy with frozen bits.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown and drain 1 pound ground beef; cover with 1 pound small curd cottage cheese.
Sprinkle over this, half a package Lawry's spaghetti sauce mix; add one 8 ounce package medium noodles, parsley, basil, salt and rest of spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover with tomatoes and water; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Replace cover and cook 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: peach cobbler(makes 33 servings)
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Spoon peaches evenly on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown (about one hour).

title: mexican roast
directions: Add water enough to Dutch oven or baking dish to cover roast. Cook 12 hours in crock-pot on low, or cook in oven at 250° for 12 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Carrots, celery, broccoli, radishes, green onion, green or yellow pepper, cherry tomatoes, black olives, cucumbers, etc.

title: benihana's chi chi mixed drink
directions: Mix in blender and pour into glass. Finish filling glass with pineapple juice. Taste like melted pineapple sherbet--yummy!

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cheese and butter. Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Mix well.
Separate rolls into 6 rectangles.
Seal perforations.

Spoon 1/3 cup meat mixture onto center of each. Pull up corners and twist slightly. Brush with melted butter. Dip in crushed croutons. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. May divide in 4 parts for larger servings using 1/2 cup chicken per square.

title: herb flavored turkey casserole
directions: In large skillet heat 3 Tbsp. margarine over medium heat. Add mushrooms and celery; cook about 5 minutes or until tender. Strain mushrooms and celery; reserving vegetables and juices.
In medium saucepan stir together cornstarch, salt thyme and pepper. Gradually stir in reserved vegetable juices and milk.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add turkey, noodles, wine, mushrooms and celery.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
In small skillet melt remaining margarine.
Add bread crumbs and stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 400 degree oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut pears to bite size pieces; cut cherries in half.
Drain fruits, reserving 2 tablespoons cherry juice.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and cherry juice.
Fold fruits and marshmallows into cream mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: caramel candy
directions: Brown sugar in an iron skillet.
Then mix in a large saucepan all ingredients except nuts.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when tested by dropping a little in cold water. Add nuts or peanut butter or both.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cool then cut into small squares.

title: taffy apple fruit dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium-size bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in bowl.

title: fish souffle
directions: Mix fish flakes, carrot, onion and green pepper (seasoned). Separate eggs.
Beat the whites until stiff and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until light yellow.
Add the yolks to fish flake mixture, then add the mashed potatoes.
Lastly fold in the egg whites.
Put in a greased baking dish.
Set dish in a pan with warm water and place on center rack of oven at 360° for 30 minutes.

title: enchiladas rojas
directions: Chop one pepper; set aside.
Coarsely chop remaining pepper and place in blender container.
Blend until smooth, scraping down sides occasionally.
Gradually whisk pureed pepper into cream cheese with Pace picante sauce and salt.
Combine chicken, chopped pepper, onions and 1/2 cup of Pace picante mixture.
Spoon a generous 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll and place seam side down in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Cover dish with wax paper.
Cook at high about 10 minutes or until hot, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 3 minutes of cooking.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish as desired.

title: weight watcher's soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon.
Add to ingredients and simmer 2 hours. Very good!

title: sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 7 minutes in 350° oven.
Line bottom of shell with hard-cooked eggs, sausage and cheeses.
Combine beaten eggs,
milk,
salt and pepper and pour over all.
Cook for 35 minutes
or until set at 350°.
Let set for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: eunice's pecan pie
directions: Beat all together well, adding pecans last.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Heat all ingredients until dissolved. Then pour over thick sliced cucumbers. You may also add sliced onions and banana peppers or green peppers, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: quick pineapple chicken
directions: Fry chicken in olive oil until white.
Add pineapple juice. Season with ginger and pepper.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Simmer until sauce is thick.
Add pineapple.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook until thick.
Stir in strawberry jello and cool, then add bananas and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shells and cool.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: dressing
directions: Fry sausage, crumble. Add to the other ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes uncovered at 350 degrees.

title: pasta salad with raisins
directions: Cook pasta shells; drain and cool.
In a large bowl, mix shells, chicken, cheese, raisins, pineapple, peas, onion and orange sections.
Chill.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine stuffing, cheese, parsley and garlic. Dip chicken parts into melted butter. Roll in stuffing mixture. Arrange in shallow baking pan. Do not crowd.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and stuffing mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pecan-crumb coffee cake
directions: In medium bowl, stir brown sugar, cinnamon and 1 cup flour. With pastry blender, cut in 6 tablespoons margarine or butter in flour mixture until looks like large crumbs.
Stir in pecans.
Set this aside.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Quickly stir in walnuts and cherries.
Turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Partially boil the cabbage enough to shrink it up.
Spread in baking dish and cover with cream of mushroom soup and slices of Velveeta cheese. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, put Durkee French fried onions on top.

title: glorified rice
directions: Turn the warm drained rice into a 3-quart bowl.
Cut marshmallows into eighths.
Use a fork to toss rice and marshmallows.
Whip the cream, then add sugar.
Turn cream over rice.
Add pineapple and fold.
Chill in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, top with cherries.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil sliced carrots and onions in water until tender.
Melt oleo and add Velveeta cheese (cut in pieces).
Mix well while melting.
Add drained veggies and mix.
Put in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding mixes and milk, then mix in Cool Whip.
Lay whole graham crackers to cover bottom of container (8 x 8-inch).
Spread pudding mixture over crackers.
Layer crackers over pudding mixture.
Spread frosting over crackers.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crabmeat.
Place in serving dish and add crabmeat.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: michael's christmas caramels
directions: Combine first three ingredients and 1 cup of the whipping cream in a heavy saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil gently for one minute.
Stir in remaining whipping cream.
Bring to a boil.
Boil to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli.
Set aside.
Cut stalks into 1 inch pieces.
Heat water to boiling.
Add broccoli, celery and onion.
Cover and heat until boiling.
Simmer until broccoli is tender.
Do not drain.
Put broccoli mixture in blender.
Cover and blend on medium until smooth.
Melt butter in a 3 quart saucepan over medium heat, stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken broth.
Heat until boiling and stir in whipping cream.
Heat until soup is hot.
Do not boil, Soup may curdle.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir egg and milk together, then layer sausage, bread, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix egg and milk together and pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; watch.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover top of cake with miniature marshmallows. Return to oven until melted.
Cool in pan.

title: crunch beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Brown beef and drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except onions.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover. Top with onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix horseradish and dry mustard well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve over cream cheese or with crackers.
You may substitute apricot preserves.

title: 7 layer overnight salad
directions: Layer spinach, lettuce, celery, onions and peas, radishes or carrots, ending with second layer of lettuce.
Seal with Miracle Whip, sour cream, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle and decorate top with bacon bits, hard-boiled eggs and tomatoes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain fat.
Add 1 quart chicken broth.
Cook slowly one hour.
Add catsup, tomato sauce, tomatoes and creamed potatoes.
Add peas, corn, butter beans, vinegar, Tabasco, mustard and chicken.
Cook slowly in crock-pot for about 6 hours.
Makes over 6 quarts.

title: potato chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; soak in cold water.
Fry ham and onions together until nicely browned.
Drain diced potatoes and place layer in bottom of stewpot; add layer of ham and onions, then sprinkle with parsley.
Repeat layers until all is
used. Cover completely with cold water.
Bring to boiling point over medium heat and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in the same pan ham and onions were cooked and add flour to make a smooth paste.
Bring chowder to boil and add thickening, stirring gently until mixture boils again.
Place two crushed soda crackers in bottom of each bowl before serving.

title: cornmeal fingers
directions: Add cornmeal gradually to boiling, salted water, stirring constantly.
Cook 20 minutes.
Turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Cut into strips 1 x 2-inches.
Split each strip in half.
Spread with butter and sprinkle again with cheese.
Place on a buttered sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: spicy meat balls in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix beef and pork. Put through food processor with steel blade until meat is smooth. Combine meat, milk, bread crumbs, salt, ginger, allspice and pepper in large bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal-cinnamon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 stick oleo.
Add seasoned crawfish, soups, rice and pimentos.
Mix well and pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes (until hot and bubbly).
Increase baking time if double recipe.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients. Spread 1 can of rolls onto the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish, sealing edges together. Spread cream cheese mixture over rolls. Place second can of rolls on top and seal edges together. Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: italian love cake
directions: With sharp serrated knife, cut cake into 3 layers.
Sprinkle each layer with 6 tablespoons Amaretto.
Place one layer on platter.
Cut pistachio ice cream into slices.
Place on bottom layer.
Top second layer with strawberry ice cream.
Top with third layer of cake.
Place in freezer.
Frost with cream or Cool Whip on top and sides of cake.
Melt chocolate bits and spread on foil. Chill until hardens.
Cut with small cookie cutter.
Top cake with chocolate decorations.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add bananas, mixing after each.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Stir in nuts and extracts, mixing well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick tests done.

title: cabbage dish
directions: Fry bacon; set aside and save grease.
Chop cabbage and onion; fry slowly in grease and add water to steam until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Put cabbage in large dish.
Break bacon, add tomato sauce and sugar to cabbage.
Put in oven at 300° until heated.

title: clam cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon.
If batter is too thin, add some cracker crumbs.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in oleo, adding garlic and saute.
Add broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Move meat to side of skillet; add soy sauce, spices, onions and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water; add to skillet and cook slowly until thickened.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot over rice.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop or grind vegetables.
Put in a large bowl.
Sprinkle salt over the vegetables.
Soak overnight.
Drain well by squeezing in palm of hands.
Add vinegar, spices tied in cloth bag and sugar to vegetables; boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in sterilized hot jars. Makes 12 pints.

title: "michigan" navy bean salad
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover with water and simmer until tender (not well done).
Drain all excess water.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: apricot bread
directions: Chop apricots and soak 30 minutes in water; drain.
Stir in sugar, butter and juices.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together; add nuts, stirring to coat.
Combine all ingredients, stirring only to mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking. Grease and flour a loaf pan; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased tube pan (10-inch).
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
When cool, frost with confectioners sugar icing.
Used crushed pineapple for part of the liquid.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides (rolled in flour).
Mix other ingredients and put a mound on each chop.
Blend mushroom soup and 1/3 cup of water.
Pour over each chop and bake for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining 1/2 can onions.
Bake another 5 minutes, uncovered, or until golden.

title: chocolate peanut clusters(made in the crock pot)
directions: Layer ingredients as listed above in large crock pot. Cover and cook on low heat for 2 hours. DO NOT LIFT LID! After two hours, stir and drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool and become firm before lifting from paper.

title: jello cake
directions: Make cake as directions on box.
Let cool.
Make jello as directions on box.
After cake cools, poke holes in top of cake with fork.
Spoon jello over top of cake.
Refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, spread Cool Whip over cake.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar and beat well.
Add softened butter, flour and cream; beat well.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold into batter and bake in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° and lower to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Put juices in bottom of 30-cup electric coffee maker.
Place sugar, salt and spices in coffee receptacle.
Brew as for coffee. Serve with or without a dollop of rum in each serving.
Makes 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Combine dry ingredients in small saucepan.
Add juice and cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute; stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots and coat evenly.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black walnut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter.
Combine flour, cornstarch and sugar; add to butter and mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Roll into 3/4 in. balls and place 1 in. apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 300° for 20-25 min. or until set.
Cool on wire racks. Dust with confectioners' sugar.
Makes 6 doz.

title: german chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Brown onion in bacon grease and then drain.
Crumble bacon and add to other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rock candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients for 1 hour until it starts to crackle, then add 1 teaspoon flavoring and food coloring of your choice.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Let cool; break into pieces.

title: pineapple no bake pie
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Combine pudding mix with whipped cream.
Beat until thick.
Beat in pineapple syrup and pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Spoon the chunk pineapple over pudding.
Glaze with cooled apricot preserves.
Chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare jello according to directions and set in refrigerator until half jelled.
Set cream cheese at room temperature in a small bowl.
Mix in sugar by hand, then add lemon juice.
Chill can of Carnation and then whip in a large bowl.
Add half jelled jello and cheese mixture to cream; blend until mixed well.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: easy blackberry crisp
directions: Mix blackberries, sugar and flour.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and sugar.
Beat until smooth and mix in melted butter. Fry on hot griddle.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar; stir in pumpkin and lemon flavoring.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend together and spread on greased and floured
cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts on top. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Dump cake on powdered sugar dusted towel.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cool.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread on large flour tortillas.
Roll up tight; chill.
Cut into slices.
Lay on plates and serve.

title: parmesan potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a baking sheet with heavy duty foil.
Cut each potato into eight wedges; place on foil.
Coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Bake for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, raisins, vanilla and carrot, then add rest of the ingredients until well blended.
Spray regular size muffin tin with vegetable spray; fill evenly with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: heath bar coffee bread
directions: Blend flour, butter and sugars.
Reserve one half of the mixture for topping.
Set reserved mixture aside.
To the other batter, add buttermilk, soda, egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburg cornbread casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain.
Season as desired.
Add milk and soup.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix. Pour or spoon cornbread batter over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: leftover roast
directions: Add roast cubes to the prepared gravy mix and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over hot mashed potatoes.
Serve with green beans and rolls.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, skin side down.
Combine garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in blender.
Turn on and add oil until coarsely chopped. Spread 1/2 of the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey. Reroll the turkey.
Tie firmly with string every 2-inches to return to original log shape.
Spread evenly with remaining garlic mixture.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
A long log shape takes less time than a more compact roast.
Remove from oven and let rest for 20 minutes before removing the strings.
Cut thin slices to serve.
Garnish.
Pour juice from meat over turkey.

title: gumbo
directions: Heat all together.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend butter
and
cup sugar;
beat in eggs one at a time. Add extract.
Mix dry ingredients together;
add to egg mixture alternately
with
milk.
Blend
just
enough to mix. Fold in lemon peel and nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix together in large casserole and sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mint truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and cool.
Combine butter and powdered sugar and cream together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add chocolate chip mix and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Add 3 capfuls mint or rum extract.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Harden in refrigerator.
Store several weeks.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Bring to a boil, then pour slowly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1 in. baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped carrots, broccoli, and cauliflower.
Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits in quarters, roll in butter then in sugar mixture.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion in large skillet.
Pour off grease.
Add vegetables and vegetable beef soup.
Simmer until vegetable are tender.
Thicken as you would gravy.
Pour into casserole.
Top with hot mashed potatoes.
Broil until browned.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix well, then pour into oblong pan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake in oblong pan according to package directions.
Combine milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake which has holes poked in the top.
Allow cake to cool, then top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: martha pafford's red-eye gravy
directions: Fry ham in oil; drain the oil off, leaving 3 tablespoons. Pour 1 cup of coffee and water into grease and ham drippings; bring to a boil.
Serve over hot grits or biscuits.

title: my favorite cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add vanilla and beat.
Sift flour and measure, then add baking soda and sift 2 more times.
Add flour to sugar and butter mixture.
Add buttermilk and beat until smooth.
Add coconut and nuts and beat some more.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour batter into 3 greased 8-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes nancy
directions: Cook potatoes only until firm; drain and cube.
Combine sour cream, milk and onion.
Place half the potatoes in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Melt butter and combine with bread crumbs.
Toss and sprinkle over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Spray 2-quart dish with Pam.
Arrange 1 1/4-inch slices in dish.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread; turn bread to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs(very good and easy)
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add the flour and salt, stirring vigorously.
Cook, continuing to stir, until the mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate when handled.
Remove mixture from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat until mixture is smooth and free from all lumps.
Drop from tablespoon onto greased baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove puffs from baking sheet, cool and fill with pudding.
Cut hole in side or top.
Can top with chocolate.
Makes 12.

title: wild rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook wild rice by directions on box.
When done, add broccoli, mushroom soup and cheese.
Pour in a casserole dish and top with stuffing mix.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour on top of stuffing. Bake at 350° until hot.

title: gingerbread
directions: In large bowl, combine brown sugar, shortening, eggs and molasses; blend well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices; gradually blend into molasses mixture.
Blend in hot water.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat; add water if needed.
This is great for chicken or turkey.
Add some relish if using for beef or pork.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and walnuts.
Pat into the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 6 ounces of Cool Whip together and spread over cool crust.
Mix the pudding with the milk and spread over the cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and walnuts.
Refrigerate between each step and when done.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add soup, broth and chicken.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add to a greased casserole dish, top with noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese and mix with cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours.
After cheese has set, mix all together and roll into balls.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Roll balls in crushed pecans.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Arrange potatoes in large shallow 3-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 425°.
Mix seasonings and sprinkle half over potatoes. Arrange chicken and sausage on top of potatoes.
Pour oil over all and sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Cover and bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Reduce to 375°, uncover and bake about 30 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are well browned.
Serve with Garlic bread and salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frosted salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare the jello using only 2 cups hot water and 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When slightly thickened, add the pineapple, bananas, marshmallows and juice of lemon. Chill until firm.

title: chicken cheese rolls
directions: Place split breasts between plastic wrap and pound to 1/2-inch thick.
Spread each with 3 tablespoons cream cheese; dot with 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Fold ends over filling.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each.
Secure with toothpick.
Place seam side down in shallow pan.
Bake at 400°
on top rack for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and done.
Broil about 5 minutes until bacon is crisp and golden.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop stems.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray pan.
Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add chopped mushrooms stems and onions; cook until tender.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill caps with stuffing.
Place mushrooms on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin tin, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: garlic string beans
directions: In large heavy saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic and beans and saute over high heat to sear beans, stirring frequently so they do not burn.
Add thyme, sea salt and pepper to taste.
Add water and vegetable bouillon.
Bring to a boil; cover tightly.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until beans are tender when pierced with tip of sharp knife.
Add more water, if necessary.
Frozen beans will take only half the time.
Add squeeze of lemon juice and toss well.
Serves 2.

title: carrot-pineapple appetizer
directions: Twirl all ingredients in blender and enjoy!!!!
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk.
Pour in casserole dish.
Add peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple and orange cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions. Let cool. Boil water and sugar until hard ball stage; dump apples and oranges in to mixture. Pour over cake and spread on frosting.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Flatten canned biscuits in bottom of casserole dish.
Put cooked, boned chicken on top.
Chop onion on top of chicken.
Cut up cream cheese on top.
Mix can of cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour on top.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together with dressing and refrigerate overnight.

title: holly taters
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Mix rest of ingredients in bag. Shake in bag.
Lay potato wedges on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Prepare crust and lattice top.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and peaches.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Cool; add lemon juice.
Put in pastry shell.
Add lattice top. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook on high until heated well.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mash potatoes.
Add 1 cup Miracle Whip and 1 teaspoon mustard and sweet pickle juice.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: fresh tomato pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss bread with butter and 2/3 of garlic.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.
Add a little salt.
Toss tomatoes with basil and rest of garlic.
Cook pasta in 4 quarts boiling water according to package directions. Add drained pasta to tomatoes and croutons.
Add freshly ground pepper.
Drizzle olive oil over and mix well. Serves 6.

title: frozen orange salad
directions: Let orange juice soften a little before combining with other ingredients.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice and serve. Serves 10 to 12.

title: peach dessert
directions: In large bowl, mix softened cream cheese and evaporated milk and set aside.
In a blender, put peaches, juice and all in blender.
In a pan, combine peach mixture, Jell-O, pineapple, sugar and water and heat until warmed.
Fold into cream cheese mixture and pour into 9 x 13 pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: chick-n-q basting sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Use as a basting sauce for chicken.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: sprite salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; add Sprite.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Drain fruit cocktail and tidbits.
Fold in.
Add extra cherries and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in stock pot and add enough water to cover. Bring to boil and simmer.
Add all ingredients and let cook until chicken is tender.
Bring pot of water to boil and add noodles, cook until tender and drain.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll the crescent rolls and layer them on the bottom of an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Pinch all the seams together to make a crust.
Bake for as long as the crescent package indicates.
Cool crust completely before assembling.

title: spinach-broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and spinach separately according to package directions.
Drain well and press excess water out of the spinach. Put broccoli in the bottom of a 6 x 9-inch glass casserole dish. Mix together sour cream and onion soup mix and spread over broccoli.
Spread the spinach over that and top with the cheese. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes.

title: banana chutney
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer about 15 minutes or until thick.

title: p. j.'s sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Go to Randall's and buy a pizza with pepperoni on it.
Take the wrapper off and put it in the oven.
Bake it at 10° about 8 minutes.
I might know more tomorrow how to do it.

title: butter crust chicken
directions: Melt margarine; add salt and flour to make medium-thick paste. Dip chicken and place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is brown and tender. The chicken does not have to be turned while baking.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients in the order given.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Roll in wax paper or press in tube pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown hamburger meat; drain, then add remaining ingredients.
Heat until mixture is warm.
Pour over Doritos and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: country potato soup
directions: Put first 6 ingredients into a large saucepan and bring it to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat until veggies are tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and spices together until light and fluffy.
Heat applesauce until hot.
Add baking soda.
Add this to creamed ingredients.
Sift flour and blend into mixture.
Add raisins, cherries and/or nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 2 hours at 275°.

title: no bake chocolate liquor treats
directions: Mix ingredients completely; roll into 1-inch balls, then in powdered sugar.
Store in icebox in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: no bake fudge nuggets
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Let stand 1-2 hrs at room temperature.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to box directions; drain.
Mix the soup, milk and pepper over medium heat.
Once mixture becomes smooth and creamy, add cut up broccoli.
After several minutes, add chicken (drained) and 1 cup grated cheese; mix well.
Add mixture to noodles in large oblong casserole dish.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining cheese; put back in oven for about 5 minutes.

title: date nut candy
directions: Cook until ropes and add dates and nuts.
Beat until it begins to harden.
Roll in damp cloth and store in icebox.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sift flour. Resift flour with soda.

Beat egg whites. Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Add flour and soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Fold in egg whites. Mix in coconut and nuts. Put in 3 prepared layer pans. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: pecan orange snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in flour, pecans, orange rind and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cool
slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blueberry dream
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter; stir well.
Set aside 2 tablespoons crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture into an ungreased 15 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Place cream cheese in large bowl; beat on high speed until fluffy. Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Set aside.
Combine whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on high, 4 minutes or until fluffy.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Spread 1/2 of topping mix over crust.
Spoon on pie filling.
Spread remaining topping. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill 8 hours.
Serves 12.

title: bloody mary
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Use a couple tablespoons mix per drink.
Add vodka, Clamato or tomato juice.
Celery stick and/or lime wedge, Tabasco, celery salt, salt and pepper can be added to taste.
Balance of mix can be refrigerated for future use.

title: coconut pies
directions: In a bowl, stir together sugar, cornstarch and egg yolks. Pour into heated milk.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture thickens.
May need to add a little more milk.
Take off heat and add 1 stick margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: ellie's mexican salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Serve at room temperature.

title: fog-free mirror
directions: Pour boiling water into a tall container, tall as needed for ears of corn.
Place 1/2 to 1 stick of butter or margarine in container of hot water.
Place on plate.
Dunk cooked corn.
No mess and butters corn all over.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Add in the eggs.
Add baking soda and baking powder.
Add bananas and sour milk.
Add vanilla. Add flour and beat until creamy.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans until 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out of loaf clean.

title: pineapple darts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, eggs, baking powder, vanilla and graham cracker crumbs slowly and mix well.
When well mixed, add enough milk or water to make batter almost as thin as cake dough.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato pork chops
directions: Season pork chops; brown and place in casserole.
Arrange sliced onion on top of chops.
Pour over tomato soup, diluted with water.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: dressing
directions: Mix well.
Pour over vegies for a marinade.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into bite-size meatballs.
Brown and drain thoroughly on paper towels.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in saucepan.
Add powdered sugar; stir to mix.
Blend in evaporated milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into quart canning jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: eggplant and almond enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and garlic.
Add salt.
Cook (stir occasionally) over medium heat for five minutes.
Add eggplant.
Mix. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add peppers, almonds and black pepper.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
Mix.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup mixture on one side and roll up.
Situate your filled enchiladas in baking pan. Pour hot sauce or salsa over top.
Heat in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Add water, bouillon cubes, tomato sauce and
Worcestershire
sauce.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, parsley and oregano.
Bring to boil, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours and serve.
If too thick, you may
add
additional bouillon or plain water.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip peanut butter in chocolate.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cut deeply around core of cabbage to loosen leaves.
Boil cabbage about 5 minutes.
Take leaves apart and allow to cool. Remove about 1 inch from rib of cabbage leaves.
Combine raw meats and add 1 cup warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll ingredients in the cabbage leaves.
Put sauerkraut in large pan. Place cabbage rolls on top.
Add water and enough tomato sauce to cover.
Cook slowly about 2 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and seasonings in bacon drippings and small amount of water until tender.
Drain well; add egg, oleo and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered casserole; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch butter pan.
Dot with butter. Cover tightly and refrigerate until 1 hour before serving time.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and return to oven for 5 or 10 minutes until melted and bubbly.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Quarter cherries and chop nuts. Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in wax paper casserole dish. Cover and wait about 1 week before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, bananas, dry ingredients and lemon juice.
Bake in two small lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: pralines
directions: Mix in large bowl the first 3 ingredients and place in the microwave for 13 minutes. Add the margarine and pecans. Stir until it starts to cool, then drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Makes about 20.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt and shape into tiny meatballs. Place in a shallow pan and broil until done, turning 1 or 2 times.

title: potato salad
directions: Rub inside of bowl with garlic clove.
Combine cut up potatoes, celery, onion, French dressing, mustard, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, some of the bacon and salt and pepper, if desired. Sprinkle remaining bacon on top and serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375 for 10-12 minutes.

title: christmas wreath punch
directions: Mix juice, syrup and ginger ale together well.
Add Christmas Ice Ring.

title: diabetes dream pie
directions: Spray a 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray (Pam). Sprinkle coconut over bottom of pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice; sprinkle pineapple over coconut.
Set aside.
Put eggs and Sweet 'N Low in a blender and blend well.
Add milk to reserved pineapple juice and pour into blender.
Add baking mix and vanilla to ingredients in blender.
Blend at medium speed until well mixed.
Pour mixture over pineapple in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until a knife inserted into middle of the pie comes out clean.
You can microwave 22 minutes, but is not as brown as when done in the oven.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon 2 or 3 times.
Set aside, pour buttermilk into the 4 cups of Raisin Bran cereal.
In large bowl beat oil with sugar, add beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Add cereal with buttermilk; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together at least 8 hours before using.
Good with potato chips, pretzels or vegetables.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Steam eggplant until tender.
Put in blender and mix in eggs, a little at a time.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix in Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet fritters(loukoumathes)
directions: Heat milk and butter to lukewarm.
Add and beat rest of the ingredients.
Let rise
until
double.
Heat
oil to 400°. Dip teaspoon in cold oil
and
drop
teaspoonfuls
into oil or scoop batter into palm of
left hand and close fist, squeezing until a rounded teaspoonful
of
dough
comes
to the surface. Drop in hot oil and fry
until	golden brown.
Drain on paper. Drizzle with honey and
sprinkle
with chopped nuts and cinnamon.

title: michael's chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepot, saut onion in olive oil until softened (4 to 5 minutes).
Add water, egg noodles and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for about 5 to 7 minutes or until noodles are softened.
Add chicken and let simmer 1 minute until chicken is heated through.
Serve warm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy's favorite jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of cake mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle the cinnamon and brown sugar on top.
Pour the remaining cake batter in pan.
Cook on 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: granny's rice pudding
directions: In the top of a double boiler, place milk and rice.
Cook over medium heat and cover when not stirring.
Stir quite often (it gives the pudding the smooth, creamy consistency).
It will take 1 to 2 hours for mixture to cook and thicken.

title: raspberry jam cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour.
Shape dough into little balls (about the size of marbles).
Poke a dent into each ball (with your thumb) and fill with jam.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and place in PAM sprayed baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Mix together the milk, onions, chilies and both cans of soup. Cook (brown) hamburger meat.
Spray pan with grease (suggest Pam). Layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole as follows:

title: hot shrimp and spinach dip
directions: Saute
the
onions
and
garlic
in butter or margarine until onions
are soft.
Combine all other ingredients except Tabasco, salt and pepper;
mix well.
Add to the onion mixture and
heat slowly,
stirring frequently, until mixture is hot. Season to taste.
Pour
into	a
chafing
dish and serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 3 cups.

title: scotch soup
directions: The night before, soak the barley and the peas until morning.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine sour cream and Miracle Whip in medium size bowl.
In a small bowl, combine last 4 ingredients, then slowly add mixture to sour cream mixture.
Blend well.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: chelo(che' lo) (rice)
directions: Rinse rice under cold running water.
Add salt and enough cold water to cover rice by 1-inch and allow to soak for at least 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Add rice to 15 cups boiling water while slowly stirring.
Continue to boil until the rice is tender.
After thoroughly draining in a strainer, rinse with cold water to remove starches.
Drain again.
In a saucepan, combine grease and 1/6 cup water.
Pour 1/4 of this mixture into the bottom of pot and add rice.
Poke a few holes in the rice, pouring the rest of the mixture over the rice and into the holes.
Wrap the lid of the pot with a dish towel and use to cover the rice.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes followed by an additional 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Serves 8.

title: mildred's praline candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Cook to a soft ball stage. Remove from fire and add 2 tablespoons butter and 2 cups pecans. Put back on fire just a few minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla or rum flavoring and soda.
Beat well and drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
It spreads thin before it sets up.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix batter
using
the
Beer
Bread
recipe.
Grease
2 cast-iron corn
bread
pans and pour batter into each section, filling about
half
full.
Top
each section with butter.
We cut off the
handles
of our corn bread pans to make it easier to stack 2
while
baking in the camp chef oven or baking in a Number 12 Dutch oven.
If baking at home, place a cookie sheet underneath as this
will drip some of the batter out.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat egg, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix oil in 1 cup warm water.
Add to same mixture.
Add flour and heat in beat in large bowl.
Grease bowl with oil.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: phil's favorite
directions: First layer:
Whip together flour and margarine with mixer. Add nuts.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Partially freeze beef, thinly sliced.
Mix all ingredients. Marinate sliced beef for at least 15 minutes.
Thread beef accordian style on bamboo skewers.
Grill approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Baste with marinade.

title: la puerta taco dip
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and 1/2 of taco seasoning.
Layer on a flat dish in following order:
cream mixture, green onions, shredded cheese, chopped tomatoes, picante sauce, olives, avocados, bacon, lettuce and more cheese.
Garnish with rest of taco seasoning.
Serve with Doritos or taco chips and large Fritos.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cook beef in crock-pot on high at least 3 hours.
Use about 2 1/2 cups of water.
About 45 minutes to 1 hour into cooking beef, add carrots and potatoes.
Heat both soups in a large saucepan. Boil noodles.
Add 2 to 3 cups of juice from beef to your soups, stirring soups good.
Drain noodles.
In 2-quart dish, place beef, carrots and potatoes, then noodles. Add soups last.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Add butter and cut with pastry blender until mixture has crumb-like texture.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and set aside. Add eggs, 1 at a time, to remaining flour mixture, blending well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in hot water, then stir into buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk into flour mixture, mixing until smooth.

title: french bread
directions: Add yeast to 1/2 cup water and stir until dissolved.
In a large bowl, dissolve sugar and salt in other 1 cup of water.
Add shortening and yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Work through dough with a spoon at 10 minute intervals for 5 consecutive times.

title: king ranch soup
directions: Mix soups, broth and Ro-Tel.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chicken, tortillas, onion and soup mix.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy beans
directions: Prepare cans of pork and beans according to amount needed. Add, according to taste, onion powder, yellow prepared mustard, brown sugar and bacon bits.
Cook on stove top or in oven until desired consistency.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan, cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons of margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and add rest of stuffing.
Toss gently and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: farfel pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs until light; gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Soak farfel in cold water; squeeze out excess water.
Add farfel, cottage cheese, sour cream, margarine, raisins and preserves to egg mixture; blend well.
Turn into a 13 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Serves 10 to 12.
A good recipe for a Seder.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and vanilla. Alternate buttermilk with flour (having soda and salt presifted into flour).
Then add nuts.
Bake at 325°.
Bake 1 hour for 2 loaves and 45 minutes for 1 loaf.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients and chill until set in mold or pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
When cool, cover top of pie with whipped cream or other whipped topping.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Pare off band of skin around middle of each.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain well.
Keep warm.
Cook peas as label directs. Drain water from cooked peas.
Sprinkle flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg over peas.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles 3 minutes.
Spoon potatoes into heated serving dish.
Pour creamed peas over potatoes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium on electric mixer.
Gradually add heavy cream.
Mix well.
Whip on high until thickened.
Place wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Using the back of a large spoon, shape mixture into ten 3 1/2-inch shells.
Freeze 2 hours or overnight.

title: bitsy's best bread
directions: Mix all the above ingredients, except French bread.
Spread mixture on French bread and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into ball. Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate until firm.

title: emergency casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Put into casserole and bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
More soy sauce may be added, if needed.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, oil, sugar and powdered sugar. Add eggs. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Chill for 30 minutes in freezer. Make 1-inch balls and press on cookie sheet with granulated sugar. (To Press: Slightly oil bottom of a glass and press in sugar, then on top of cookie ball. For thinner cookies, press flatter.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat into pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Split cake in half.
Crumble in bowl.
Top with 1/2 Kahlua, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 Heath bar candy.
Repeat the process on top of first.
Chill until ready to serve.
Scoop out into dessert dishes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Beat in one egg at a time. Alternate flour and 7-Up, ending with flour.
Add all extracts. Beat well.
Put into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and take out of pan.
Yields 15 servings.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: humdingers
directions: Melt sugar and oleo in a saucepan on medium heat.
Add dates; stir 5 to 8 minutes.
In a large bowl put Rice Krispies and nuts. Add date mixture and vanilla; stir well.
Pinch off enough to roll the size of a walnut in palm of hand.
Then roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 60.

title: mexican skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients, except spaghetti.
Bring to a boil and add uncooked spaghetti.
Simmer, covered, until spaghetti is tender (25 to 30 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: kolacky cookies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out thin to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in cookie shapes.
Make print in center and fill with filling.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half prior to baking for one hour or until done. (Note: This recipe uses baking sized potatoes so adjust as needed if not using potatoes this large.) Once potatoes are baked, allow to cool and when they are cool enough to handle, scoop the potato out of the skin leaving the skin as a shell to be used later. In a large mixing bowl, add potato pulp and all ingredients listed above. (Adjust spices to your own taste.) Mix all ingredients using either a blender or with a fork depending on how fine you want the potatoes mashed. Once the ingredients have been mixed together, place them back in to the potato skins. Heat oven to 350 and bake potatoes an additional 10 to 15 minutes until the tops are browned.

title: rigatoni casserole
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, saute beef, onion and garlic until beef is browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
In a bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, milk and salt.
Add rigatoni.
Toss to coat well.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown beef; drain and set aside.
In the same saucepan, saute onions, carrots, celery, basil and parsley in 1-tablespoon butter until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add broth, potatoes and beef; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 - 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Meanwhile, in a small skillet, melt remaining butter.
Add flour; cook and stir 3 - 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add to soup and bring to boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese, milk, salt and pepper, cook and stir until cheese melts. Remove from heat; blend in sour cream.
Yields 8 servings (2 1/4 quarts).

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with whisk; add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells that have been baked about 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle pecans evenly into pie shell before pouring liquid ingredients into shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This pie is not too sweet.

title: squash sour cream casserole
directions: Pour melted butter over crumbs and mix well.
In separate bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Put a layer of crumbs in bottom of baking dish.
Reserve same amount to place on top.
Mix remaining crumbs with squash mixture and spoon into dish.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer squash
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.

title: spinach pin rolls
directions: Thaw, drain and squeeze spinach (so it's got the water off it).
Mix everything together, except tortillas, and add spinach. Spread on tortillas (kind of thick).
Roll, cover well and refrigerate for 1 to 2 days before serving.
Cut and serve. (Saran Wrap each roll individually.)

title: sweet relish
directions: Chop cukes, onion, green and red peppers and celery.
Let stand overnight in salt and 2 quarts of water.
Drain in the a.m.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Freeze 1/2 c. miniature marshmallows. Place chocolate and butter in large bowl.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Mix in tomato soup, salt, pepper and garlic. Set aside.

title: bacon ranch dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 1 hour. Good with Ruffles chips.

title: applesauce raisin nut bread
directions: Combine baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, sour cream and applesauce to butter and sugar mixture; mix well.
Blend in flour mixture.
(Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.)
Mix in raisins and chopped walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Decorate top of loaf with 6 walnut halves.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until wire cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto a rack and cool completely.

title: pepper corn
directions: Mix ingredients well. Place in flat casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison round steak
directions: Wipe steaks clean with damp cloth.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and pound well into the steak.
Brown both sides of steak and any remaining seasoned flour slowly in the heated butter.
Add 1/4 cup of water.
Cover and simmer slowly, adding the rest of the water as needed, 1 to 2 hours.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in the sour cream and cook 2 minutes longer. Serve at once.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown beef and onion, drain. Mix in sauce and spread in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over beef mixture.
In bowl mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 425° oven until centers are soft (or microwave).
Cut thin lengthwise slices from top of each, or cut each in half lengthwise.
Scoop out, carefully reserving shell. Mash potato, add butter, milk, seasoning and onion.
Spoon back into shell.
Scatter 1 tablespoon cheese over each.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place potatoes on tray; at this point may refrigerate up to 8 hours.
Bake at 425° until hot, about 40 minutes.
Great time saving make ahead!

title: schee or cabbage soup
directions: Cook 5 or 6 hours.
We cook this in an electric roaster.
It can be cut in half or less and cooked in a smaller container.
The meat is removed and served separately with mustard.
After one meal, we freeze the rest of the soup in quart and 2-quart plastic containers.
This recipe came from Dr. Alfred Mihachik's mother.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar ahead of time.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: toad's cheese ball
directions: Grind beef and onion in food processor or blender.
Then add to cream cheese and mix well.
Form into 2 or 3 balls.
Roll in pecans.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp pealue
directions: Melt margarine in large pan; saute onion, garlic, celery, and green onions. Add soups, raw rice, and shrimp; salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli.
Layer all ingredients in large greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Spread Durkee onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: In large bowl, cream the sugar and butter together.
Beat well.
Add flour and the 4 egg yolks and beat well.
Add grated rind and juice of the lemons added to the sugar and flour mixture and beat; add the milk and mix.
Last, beat the egg
whites and fold into the lemon mixture.
Pour into two unbaked pie pastry and bake at 375°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; mold onto plate.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place chicken in single layer in baking dish; cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain and wash baking dish.
In saucepan, combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Place small amount of tomato mixture in bottom of baking dish. Cover with either cooked noodles or rice.
Add chicken.
Pour remaining tomatoes over; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and return to oven for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes or until Mozzarella cheese is melted.

title: squash pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until set in the middle, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make the cake and let it cool.
Take a fork and punch holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk onto and into cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle abundantly with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together 2 times and add to mixture.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and sugar to rolling boil and boil for 1 minute only.
Then dump in oatmeal, peanut butter, coconut and mix.
Add the vanilla and stir.
Drop on wax paper.
Enjoy!
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Place in a 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft-ball stage.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cut into squares.

title: mercy's messy nachos
directions: Layer large platter with chips.
Heat chili and layer on chips.
Heat Cheez Whiz and layer.
Chop onions, lettuce and tomato and sprinkle on top.
Spread sour cream in middle.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a large dish.
Spread mayonnaise over layers before the cheese, then layer cheese and bacon across top.

title: star croutons
directions: You will also need 1 small star shaped cutter.

title: egg-ham and cheese bake(serves 8 to 10 people)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube 10 slices of bread.
Cut 1/2 pound cheese into small chunks. Dice ham into small cubes.
Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.

title: indian relish
directions: Use meat grinder and grind up fine tomatoes, red peppers, green peppers, cabbage and onions.
Add salt; set overnight.
In the morning, drain ground vegetables.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Make a bag from a clean handy wipe and add 1 tablespoon whole cloves and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Use a twist tie to hold.
Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour mixture into hot, sterile jars and seal.
Yields about 7 quarts.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add 1/2 cup self-rising flour; mix well.
Then add coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: seafood bake
directions: Mix the seafood, green pepper, onion, celery and mayonnaise. Place 1/2 bread cubes in casserole, a layer of mixture, then the rest of cubes.
Combine the eggs, milk and soup; pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Let set, unbaked, in refrigerator overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot 6 hours or until done.
(Takes less than 6 hours.)

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: turkey supreme
directions: Fold together ingredients.
Cover top with 1 cup crushed potato chips and 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: bulgogi (korean steak)
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and Coke.
Add sliced beef.
Cover and chill in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Add other ingredients and mix with hands.
May grill outside or in frying pan.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Drain the pineapple juice in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend in ketchup, soy sauce, brown sugar and garlic.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once or twice while cooking.
Use toothpicks to serve.

title: supreme chocolate pie
directions: Mix chocolate pudding with 3 cups milk and set aside.
Cream 8 ounce package of cream cheese (room temperature) with powdered sugar and half Cool Whip.
Put into chocolate batter and mix in large bowl.
Use remaining Cool Whip for topping of pies. Refrigerate.

title: heritage ham casserole
directions: Prepare white sauce, add Velveeta, and stir until melted.
Add green pepper, mushrooms, onion and pimento.
Combine cooked spaghetti with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and toss to coat spaghetti. Layer spaghetti into a 12 x 9 buttered baking dish, then add ham and sauce mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6-8.

title: tracy's easy cinnamon buns
directions: Thaw 2 loaves frozen bread.
Tear or cut into equal sized pieces.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar to melted butter and stir well.
Add vanilla pudding, milk, cinnamon and nuts and raisins if desired.
Pour over bread.
Let rise 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
As soon as you take them out of oven, turn them out onto another pan.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Beat egg with a fork.
Melt margarine.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Cut out like biscuits.
Place in pan and let stand at room temperature for at least 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wasetti
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown meat and butter in skillet.
Add soup and simmer.
Add cheese and melt good.
Mix together in baking dish and bake at 400° until it bubbles.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.

title: creamed onions in wine sauce
directions: Boil onions 25 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Cook next 5 ingredients together and add onions.
Transfer to serving dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese or other shredded cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all and heat.
Cook down.
Make with Ham, Chops, Chicken, or Short Ribs.
Double if doing a lot.

title: good and easy cookies
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil.
Lay whole graham crackers on foil.
Sprinkle walnuts on crackers.
Boil oleo and sugar for 2 minutes.
Spoon over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes exactly.
Cool and break into sections.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large skillet; drain well.
Add garlic salt, oregano, pepper, tomatoes, tomato paste and water. Simmer 30 minutes.
