Layer half the noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella, Velveeta and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat the layers with the remaining half.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Stir together boiling water and jello until dissolved.
Let set in freezer until egg white consistency.
Mix cranberry sauce and lemon juice with jello.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and freeze. Mix together powdered sugar, mayonnaise, nuts and Cool Whip. Spread over frozen jello mixture and freeze until served.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; let set for a few minutes, then roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Add everything but turkey to water and bring to a boil.
Boil about 5 minutes and let cool.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Inject liquid deep into turkey all over with a large needle and syringe. Rub paste from cheesecloth over turkey and store in plastic bag in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
In large 10 gallon pot, heat 5 gallons or 35 pounds oil over gas burner outside to 350°.
Remove all plastic from turkey (pop up timer, plastic on legs).
Wire legs together with heavy wire.
Drop turkey into oil.
Turkey should float in about 30 to 40 minutes.
Check temperature in thigh with meat thermometer to 180°.
Remove from oil; let drip over paper towels.

title: frosted chewies
directions: Place sugar and syrup in a large pan; heat until sugar dissolves stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stir well.
Add cereal.
Press into buttered 11 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Melt chocolate chips; spread on top of cereal mix.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: faye's broccoli dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Serve with favorite crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Pour into graham cracker shell.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a medium bowl; stir well until completely blended.
Use a fork to do this.
Serve with raw vegetables colorfully arranged.
Use celery, carrots, turnip strips, mushrooms, cauliflower, broccoli, Jerusalem artichokes, cucumbers, etc.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter and chips over hot water.
Cool; beat eggs until thick and lemon colored. Stir and beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate mixture and vanilla. Stir in flour.
Pan must be 8-inches and well-greased.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a small bowl, combine orange juice, lime or lemon juice and honey.
Pit and coarsely chop nectarine.
(Or peel peach, if desired, and chop.)
Add nectarine or peach to fruit juice mixture.
Bias-slice banana into 1/4-inch pieces; add to fruit juice mixture.
Remove seeds from melon and cut into 12 thin slices.
Cut off peel.
On 4 individual dessert plates, fan the melon slices.
Top each serving with 1/4 of the fruit mixture.
If desired, sprinkle with pine nuts and garnish with a lime peel curl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut and vanilla. Add peanut butter and powdered sugar in small amounts and mix well.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Lay on waxed paper. Chill in refrigerator.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat; add garlic. Cook until golden.
Stir in crushed tomatoes and parsley.
Add zucchini; season with salt and pepper.
Cover; reduce heat and cook 20 to 30 minutes or until al dente.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Add all ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven, about 350°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cake long ways.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 1/2 cup M&M's in mix, then arrange on top.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: choco-holic's favorite popcorn
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Simmer gently to soft ball stage (242°).
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, melt chocolate and add with butter to the syrup; mix well.
Pour over lightly salted, popped corn, stirring to coat all kernels.
Spread out on greased pan to cool and separate kernels.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine above ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili dip
directions: Cook hamburger; add other ingredients and beat until cheese melts.
Don't add salt!

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer potatoes in margarine.
Mix sour cream, onion, chicken soup, salt and pepper in bowl.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup margarine with cornflakes in bowl.
Sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Mix together with mayonnaise and small amount of mustard. Place filling on meat slice and roll up.
Hold with toothpick.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar and flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Put flour on hands and roll dough in small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Place on wax paper and chill.

title: baked chicken-stove top dressing
directions: Brown chicken pieces; put in casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sherry or water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Make Stove Top as directed on box. Pour over chicken; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: robin's chicken casserole
directions: Coat bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, soup, chiles and sour cream in large bowl. Layer rice on bottom of pan; place chicken mixture over rice. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Add cheese and chips; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no fuss lasagne
directions: In a large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, spaghetti sauce mix, sugar, parsley, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a bowl, combine eggs with cottage cheese, 1/2 of Cheddar cheese and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake by directions and add coconut flavoring.
Bake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove cake from oven.
Cool slightly.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour over cake slowly.
Mix Cool Whip with coconut.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir until completely dissolved, then pour in blender. Add cream cheese. Blend. Pour into bowl. Add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef in skillet.
Saute onions in small saucepan.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 1 hour.

title: hobo breakfast
directions: Cover bottom of large skillet with oil.
Add onions.
Saute for 2 mins. on medium heat.
Add potatoes.
Cover and cook until desired tenderness, stir with spatula occasionally.
Fold in sausage.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Cover and cook until eggs are done (3-5 mins.)
Remove from heat, top with shredded cheese. Cover to let cheese melt.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add vanilla, sugar and thawed strawberries, juice and all.
Continue beating for 15 minutes.
Add Cool Whip, folding into mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been lined with crushed vanilla wafers.
Add more crumbs to top.

title: cranberry apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boil.
Cool; add everything else. Chill before serving.
Garnish punch bowl with sliced lemons, limes and fresh strawberries.

title: drunken stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in large baking pot or casserole. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice (cooked).
Do not brown meat.

title: smoky mountain chicken
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon.
Place on grill (or in oven).
Cook until almost done.
While cooking, mix barbecue sauce, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Put sauce on chicken.
Turn twice, then put on Swiss cheese.
Let cheese melt.
Remove from grill.
Top with tomatoes and onions.
Serve.

title: easy cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish melt butter or margarine.
In medium bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Then add milk. Pour this over the melted margarine, then pour fruit over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: mama's baked chili spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown onions in shortening.
Mix all, except cheese, and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Serve hot.

title: dirt cake
directions: Take the white out of the Oreos.
Dip the cookies in milk. Alternate a layer of cookies and a layer of Cool Whip, ending with cookies.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add buttermilk, oil and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Spoon batter into a 9-inch round cake pan coated with vegetable cooking spray and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar and garnish with strawberries or any fruit you wish.

title: potato balls
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling unsalted water about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and mash. Stir in Parmesan cheese, cream cheese, butter or margarine, green onion, onion soup mix and pepper. Mix well.

Add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk if mixture is dry. Shape mixture into 8 balls. Dip in beaten egg and roll in cornflakes. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and crispy.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook all ingredients, except nuts, in skillet until brown (approximately 10 minutes).
Stir constantly.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with nuts.
Pour cooked mixture into pan, over nuts. Top nuts and mixture with Hershey chocolate bars.
The heat from the mixture will melt the chocolate.
Spread the melted chocolate with a spatula.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers and cut into large chunks. In ovenproof baking dish that can be used on top of stove, saute green peppers in oil until they begin to soften.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Take peppers out of dish and set aside. Brown sausage in same baking dish.
When browned, add red wine. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Uncover and add peppers.
Bake an additional 30 minutes and serve in same baking dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: freezer salad
directions: Shred cabbage; put tablespoon of salt over and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Shred carrot and pepper; add to cabbage.
Cook, boil 1 minute, then cool to lukewarm, whole mustard seed, vinegar, celery seed, water and sugar.
Mix vegetables and syrup together. May keep in refrigerator or put in containers and freeze.

title: claudia macik's lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook lasagne according to package directions; drain.
Combine Ricotta, Parmesan, 1 cup of Mozzarella, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 layers of cake.
Crumble 1 into bottom of punch bowl. Use 1 box of pudding which has been mixed according to directions. Layer 1 can drained pineapple.
Add pie filling, then Cool Whip. Repeat with other ingredients.
Top with cherries and nuts. Should be made the day to be served.
Store in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie - no crust
directions: Put in blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let set 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put coconut on top after setting.

title: four fruit pizza
directions: Soften cookie dough to room temperature. Pat it into a 12-inch pizza pan and bake in conventional 375° oven for 15 to 16 minutes; cool.

title: doris bauer's calico beans
directions: Brown meat with onions and bacon and cook these ingredients slowly.
Add beans, mustard, catsup and sugar.
Mix together. Bake about 40 minutes at 350° (if freezing, don't bake first).

title: biscuits
directions: Mix cream & flour. Drop by spoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: fudge
directions: Cook chocolate pudding, milk and butter to a rolling boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add the powdered sugar and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan, or drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Put all sauce ingredients (tomatoes through crushed red pepper) in a Dutch oven or slow cooker and simmer until desired thickness. Place bread in a bowl and pour enough water over to dampen.
Let soak, then squeeze out moisture.
Mix together in large bowl the bread and meatball ingredients (hamburg through black pepper). Form into balls.
Put into simmering sauce to cook.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With a fork, beat eggs slightly. Lightly mix in meat, crumbs, onion and green pepper.
Combine other ingredients.
The secret is to mix well, but lightly.
Do not pack.
In baking dish, shape meat into oval loaf.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: butterfly cupcakes
directions: Make pudding according to package directions, using skim milk. Let set for 5 minutes.
Cut a cone shape from the top of each cupcake and set aside.
Fill cavity of each cupcake with 1 tablespoon pudding.
Cut cones in half and place two halves, flat side down, on each cupcake to represent butterfly wings.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of jam in the center to resemble the body.
Dust with powdered sugar (optional).

title: rainbow jello squares
directions: Mix 1/4 cup cold water with 1 package Knox gelatine.
Mix 3/4 cup boiling water with 1 package of Jell-O.
When dissolved, mix in softened Knox.
Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Mix 1 cup cold water with 2 packages Knox gelatine.
Add 1 cup boiling water mix.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix.
Pour 1 cup milk mixture onto Jell-O.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Repeat layers, 7 layers in all.
Set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg until fluffy.
Combine with the remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into 1/2 to 1-inch balls and press flat.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on parchment lined cookie sheets.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk, potatoes, raisins, coconut, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir a few times while baking.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and 1 cup bread crumbs. Mix well.
Roll individual patties in remaining bread crumbs and fry in butter until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In large bowl, mix ground beef, taco seasoning and refried beans.
On large platter or 2 small ones, spread meat mixture.
Spread on sour cream, then avocado dip.
Sprinkle on olives, then Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pile shredded cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans and ham hocks in Dutch oven or large pot.
Cover with water until pot is 3/4 full.
Add Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper, using 5 shakes of each.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 3 hours or longer.
(Beans should be cooked to a soft consistency.)
Add water as needed.

title: cranberry frost
directions: Divide 1 quart lemon sherbet among 8 small glass cups or footed goblets; freeze until serving time.
Just before serving, pour 1 quart cranberry cocktail over sherbet.

title: hot fruit brunch casserole(quick and easy, a family favorite!)
directions: In a casserole dish, put pie filling in first.
Next, add drained peaches and pears.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top and then pour rum over it.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6. Can easily be doubled for a larger crowd.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Divide dough in half; color portions of one-half with food colors.
Cover dough; chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: best yet beef stew
directions: Cook stew beef and onions with water in crock-pot on low all day.
Add tomatoes, carrots, potatoes, bouillon, basil, Sweet 'N Low, salt and pepper.
You may thicken with cornstarch or flour, if desired.

title: brandy sauce
directions: Boil the several parts of the entire head and the feet in the same way as for souse; all must be boiled so perfectly tender that the meat will separate easily from the bones.
After neatly separated, chop the meat fine while warm, seasoning with salt, pepper, sage or other spices to taste; put in a strong bag.
Place a weight on it and let it remain until cold, or put it in any convenient dish, placing a plate with weight on it to press the meat; cut in slices.
Roll in flour and fry in lard or serve cold.

title: apple oat bran muffins(healthful eating)
directions: In a small bowl, combine oat bran, whole wheat flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs; stir in molasses.
Mix in olive oil, apple juice concentrate and skim milk.
Gradually add flour mixture using a wire whisk.
Mix ingredients just until moistened.
Stir in chopped apples and raisins.
Pour into paper-lined muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out dry.

title: grandma taylor's brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add cocoa, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into sprayed pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and mushroom in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat, stirring occasionally (can also add peas).
Serve over toast or rolls.

title: pineapple bran muffins
directions: Combine All-Bran, milk, pineapple and raisins.
Add shortening and egg.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, soda and brown sugar.
Add to first mixture and mix until dampened.
Divide dough evenly between 12 paper lined muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 24 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press first 2 ingredients into oblong pan and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.
Beat next four ingredients together on high for 5 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham crust. Next, spread on 2 medium cans pineapple, drained.
Slice 2 to 3 bananas on top of that and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top and refrigerate.

title: apricot pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the apricots and lemon juice. Lightly mix in all remaining ingredients and let stand 15 minutes. Use your favorite pastry or prepared pie shell or following recipe.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: whole wheat crust salmon pie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup cheese, salt and paprika.
Cut in butter. Add almonds.
Reserve 1 cup of crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining into 10-inch pie plate.

title: dingbats
directions: Melt butter, sugar and egg in pan until dissolved.
Add dates and cook on low 10 minutes.
Add pecans and cook 5 more minutes. Remove and add vanilla, Rice Krispies one cup at a time.
Let cool and roll in balls in coconut.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: Cook whole baby carrots, using microwave or stove top directions.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until preserves melt. Stir in carrots and cook until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with apricot halves.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and chill until you can roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
You can make these ahead and roll into balls and freeze.
Put them in Ziploc bags for later use.
You can take them right out of the freezer and bake at the same temperature and time as fresh.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions in package.
Boil and drain.
Brown meat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add macaroni, tomatoes with liquid, corn, olives, chili powder, oregano, salt, pepper and taco sauce.
Pour in 3-quart casserole.
Top with corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on meat.
Brown on both sides in hot oil, use Dutch oven.
Add 1/2 cup water and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove fat.
Add vegetables and rest of water.
Pour on tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the ketchup.
Form into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Add 1/4 cup ketchup to the top of loaf and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, discarding stems.
Pat dry.
Tear into pieces and put in salad bowl.
Add egg, cheese, bacon and mushrooms. Gently toss to mix well.
Coat with salad dressing; top with croutons.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased bread pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add cornbread mix.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green sauce for pasta
directions: Mix in blender.
Cook pasta of choice and combine with sauce.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Put cranberry sauce in a boiler.
Add dry Jell-O.
Heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Set aside and let cool.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Mix and put into a dish or mold.
Let gel until firm.
Ready to serve!

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush cookies, reserve 1 c. Melt butter and pour over remaining crushed cookies; mix well.
Press down crushed cookie mix in 9 x 13

pan. Mix sugar, 1 c. cool whip and cream cheese with mixer. Spread over crumbs, refrigerate. Make pudding according to direction. Layer on top of cool whip, then add remaining cool whip. Sprinkle reserve cookies on top. Chill for 1 hour.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets with Crisco. Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Place sheets of foil on counter top. Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add seasonings.
Serve hot over buttered toast or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo until tender.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cheese that has been grated.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add rice and chopped broccoli.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: pasta with asparagus and creamy lemon sauce
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water 4 minutes. Add asparagus; cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk. Roll nuts, dates and candy in flour. Add coconut. Add to batter and cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Mix with other ingredients and freeze in cubes or rings until needed. Before using, let thaw to form slush. Place in punch bowl and add 2 or 3 large bottles of ginger ale.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.

title: country buttermilk pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan and dust well with flour.
Shake out excess.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter in large bowl for 2 minutes with an electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until yellow disappears.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat iron skillet with 2 tablespoons oil in it.
Pour batter into skillet and bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean. Can be baked in muffin tins or cake pan.

title: lady locks
directions: Mix together flour, eggs, ice water and salt like pie dough. Knead with hands and chill 1 hour.
Make a spreading mixture by combining the crisco, oleo and cornstarch.
Cut dough into 4 parts.
Roll out, 1 part at a time, and spread with some of the spreading mixture.
Fold dough like an envelope and refrigerate 1 hour.
Repeat this procedure 3 times with each dough.
Then roll dough very thin and cut in 1x6 inch strips and roll on a clothespin that is covered with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.
Remove from oven and slip shells off the pins.
Allow to cool and fill with cream filling (recipe to follow).

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop onto cookie sheets and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.
The finished cookies will be semi-soft.
Makes 28 cookies.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
Put orange slices if desired.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut green pepper into 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Thinly slice carrot; set aside.
Mince garlic; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid into 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Stir in honey, red wine vinegar and soy sauce; set aside.
For batter, in a mixing bowl, combine egg and water.
Add cornstarch, flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Dip chicken cubes in batter and deep fry in hot oil until golden.
Drain and keep chicken warm.
Preheat a wok or large skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry garlic 30 seconds.
Add green pepper and carrot; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes. Stir pineapple juice mixture into vegetables.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add chicken and pineapple chunks; heat thoroughly. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mother's lemon pie filling
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in double boiler. Beat egg yolks until light and add with water to dry ingredients.
Cook about 10 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon rind and juice. Cool slightly before pouring into baked pie shell. Top with meringue. Delicious!

title: escort chicken
directions: Melt 1/2 of the butter in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of the crackers, crushed.
Put chicken in next.
Sprinkle chestnuts over chicken.
Mix soups and sour cream together.
Pour over.

title: easy white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup very warm water and 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Add 2 2/3 cups warm water in large bowl, 1 tablespoon salt, 3 tablespoons shortening and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add flour, 3 cups at a time until 9 to 10 cups are used.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Pinch off pieces the size of small balls. Makes 36 rolls or 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: short-cut cheese bread
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, milk, butter and chives, cooking and stirring until butter melts.
In a large mixing bowl, combine this mixture and bread mix.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (5 to 10 minutes), adding additional flour, if necessary.
Invert bowl over dough; let rest for 25 minutes. Shape dough into a loaf and place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 225° for 20 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 425° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more.
Cover pan with foil for the last 10 minutes of baking, if bread browns too quickly.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and mix in next 4 ingredients.
Place one ham slice and one cheese slice in each roll.
Pour butter mixture over rolls.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes

title: korvkaka(liver pudding)
directions: Cook rice in milk in top of a double boiler until just about done.
Let it cool.
Grind meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients and place in a buttered casserole.
Bake until firm, about 1 hour. Serve hot with melted butter and lingonberries.

title: banana dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/4 cup butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, one cup butter and powdered sugar.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Layer in order bananas, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 hours.

title: grandma mccarthy's bread pudding
directions: Bring milk to boiling point (but don't boil).
Add margarine and bread.
Let stand until cool.
Mash bread with potato masher until custard-like.
Grease 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish with margarine.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place confectioners sugar and milk in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring to boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Don't be surprised if this stage takes 30 minutes (or longer).
Once boiling, stir continuously for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate to cool.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: artichoke shrimp and mushroom marinade
directions: Combine mushrooms, artichokes and shrimp.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over shrimp mixture.
Marinate overnight or longer in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: In bottom
of 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter, brown sugar and rhubarb.
In
bowl,
cream
Crisco,
cup sugar and egg. Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix well together and pour over rhubarb mixture in pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for
to
45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then invert on serving dish.

title: all american macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 4 cups.

title: amaretto bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Place in medium size bowl and cover with half and half.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and chilies and set aside.
Butter a casserole dish and line with tortillas which have been torn into pieces.
Put a layer of chicken, then sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers until gone.
Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour or until well heated.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place drained pineapple in baking dish (8-inch square). Combine sugar, flour and cheese. Add pineapple juice. Spread mixture over pineapple. Melt butter or margarine in frying pan. Add as many Ritz crackers as it takes to absorb melted butter. Sprinkle this evenly over casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding milk in small amounts.
Mix well.
Add salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Make balls the size of large marble.
Flatten out.
Place cherry in and wrap around it.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over boiling water.
Dip balls and drain on wax paper.

title: bryan sandwiches
directions: Defrost loaves in microwave according to label directions. Stretch one loaf out in a large casserole pan or cookie sheet. Layer with remaining ingredients.
Now place stretched 2nd loaf over top.
Seal edges.
Brush with butter.
Cok for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: denise's edible eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; slice it in 1-inch slices.
Salt it both sides and let it sit 20 minutes.
Chop onion and saute in oil and spices until half cooked.
Rinse eggplant well and cut into squares.
Add eggplant to onion; saute on low heat 10 minutes.
Add can of tomatoes; saute 10 more minutes.
Put this mixture into casserole dish; add cheese and microwave or bake until cheese is melted.

title: simple bundt cake
directions: Beat all together in an electric mixer for about 20 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Test with a toothpick for doneness.
It will come out clean if cake is done.
Cool for 5 minutes in pan. Turn out onto a cake plate and drizzle with icing.

title: toffee-nut bars
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening and sugar.
Stir in flour. Press mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, using hand to flatten and cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Then spread with Almond-Coconut Topping.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine both kinds of cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine flour, cornbread, sugar, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with fingers until mixture is crumbly. Add milk and egg; beat with hand electric mixer for 1 minute.

title: potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes (large chunks).
Shake cubes of potatoes in a bag with Parmesan cheese, flour, salt and pepper. Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Turn once after half an hour.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Boil ingredients, except fruit, until syrupy.
Then add washed and peeled fruit and cook until soft.
Can or freeze.

title: double dip brownies
directions: Prepare brownies as usual, then add Bake Top and bake following directions on package.
Glaze and serve.

title: aunt susan's lemonade
directions: Cook sugar and water 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add fruit juices and peel.
Pour over mint leaves.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Strain into jar and keep in refrigerator.
Use 1/3 cup syrup for each glass.
Fill with crushed ice and water.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine cider and juices in a kettle.
Tie cloves and allspice in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to cider with nutmeg and cinnamon sticks.
Add brown sugar gradually to suit taste.
Red food coloring may be added, if desired.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove spice bag.
Serve hot in mugs.
Serves 24.

title: stew
directions: Boil pork and chicken together.
When done, cool and debone, pulling off excess fat.
Work meat up together real good.
Cook potatoes and onions where meat was cooked.
After they are cooked, add other ingredients, except corn.
Add corn not long before done.
Best cooked several hours on low.

title: perozhki
directions: Mix butter and flour together.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add sour cream, vanilla and lemon.
Beat this into butter and flour mixture.
Turn completed mixture onto a floured board and shape into balls the size of marbles.
Chill overnight.

title: green tortillas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot oil for an instant, then in soup.
Layer 3 tortillas with hamburger, cheese, onion and chilies.
Repeat.
When all is used, pour remaining soup over and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350° the tortillas with cheese on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in enough water to plump.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Then add soda dissolved in raisin water.
Mix raisins and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Important to dissolve soda in raisin water first.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well!
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water. Yields 40 cups.

title: baltimore peach cake
directions: Sprinkle yeast into very warm water in a bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Thoroughly cream margarine with sugar in a large electric mixer bowl.
Add yeast mixture, eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Beat at medium speed until blended (45 seconds).
Spread in well-greased 9-inch square pan.

title: italian pita
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pita pocket.
Stuff into pita pocket.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Place washed chicken thighs in a bowl; pour in white wine and garlic.
Marinate 1 1/2 hours.
Blend apricots, tarragon and dill in blender.
Place chicken in Pam-coated pan.
Brush on sauce. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water; bring to boil.
Set aside to cool. Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins last.
Spread thin on greased and floured jellyroll pans.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes. Ice while hot with icing of 10x sugar and water.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, milk and dry ingredients.
Roll out on a floured surface and cut with cookie cutter.
Place 1 teaspoonful of filling on each cookie and place another cookie on top that has a hole in it.
Press edges together. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pat's perfect sesame noodles
directions: Combine sesame oil and canola oil in a saucepan.
Add the garlic and ginger and saute until soft.
Do not allow to become crisp and brown.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, hot oil and sugar; boil for a few seconds.
Remove from heat.
Cook pasta, then rinse thoroughly with cold water.
Drain.
Mix noodles with sauce and toss.
Toss noodles occasionally so they all get a chance to marinate in sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, bring to room temperature.
Sprinkle with cilantro.

title: sugar-free carrot cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Beat eggs in large mixing bowl. Add sugar, water and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add slowly to	egg mixture, mixing well.
Add carrots, pecans and pineapple. Mix
until	well
combined.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with
vegetable spray.
Flour lightly.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Sugar-Free Cream Cheese Icing.

title: adam's favorite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs; mix.
Sift flour, pudding and soda and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add almond extract, oats and Heath bar crunches.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on nonstick cookie sheet.
Remove before just quite done.
Let set on cookie sheet to cool slightly. Makes a bunch of yummy cookies!

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marinated tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Combine tomato wedges, cucumber slices and onion rings in a large bowl; set aside.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix cheese, sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with about 2 cups of cheese flavored crackers.
Drizzle with oleo.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut onions 1/4-inch thick.
Dip into mixture and drop into hot oil.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together until lightly browned. Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook pork.
Add onions and celery and brown.
Add flour. Cover with water and simmer with La Choy brown gravy sauce.
When celery is almost tender, add last four ingredients.
Heat only until warm.
Serve with rice and/or chop suey noodles.
Use soy sauce as desired.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add egg, oil, honey and milk to dry ingredients; mix until combined. If you want plain muffins, spoon a little into greased muffin tin at this point.

title: kansas fried chicken
directions: Preparation:Preheat oil in large electric skillet at 350 degrees.
Rinse chicken pieces and place in a bowl
to begin batter process.
Place flour, bread crumbs and lightly mixed eggs into separate shallow bowls.
Add garlic, salt, and pepper to flour bowl.

title: italian pepperoni cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In large sauce pan combine water and shortening, bringing to a boil. Add all of the flour and stir vigorously. Cook and stir until mix forms a ball.
Remove form heat.
Cool 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition. Stir in all the rest of the ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon, 2 inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 48.

title: dump cake
directions: Put ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in order given. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cucumber "garlic" salad(this is a great addition to any meal and should bring raves)
directions: Layer cucumbers, onion and garlic in a large bowl.
Salt each layer generously.
Mix very gently with fork.
Let stand about 1 hour, then gently by hand, squeeze out liquid (there will be quite a lot).
Discard liquid.
Mix in Miracle Whip to taste, about 1/2 to 1 cup or more.
Chill and serve.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease off before starting rice.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla, apples, nuts and coconut.
Mix and pour in greased tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until done.
Due to heavy batter, is easier mixed by hand than with mixer.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt 1/2 cup butterscotch pieces and 1/4 cup butter, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Add flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and egg to butterscotch mixture in saucepan.
Mix well.
Fold marshmallows, chocolate pieces and chopped nuts into butterscotch batter just until combined, about 5 strokes.
Spread in greased pan.

title: party pizzas ii
directions: *May need 2 depending on how much sauce you like.

title: miniature spinach frittatas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat the cups in a miniature muffin pan lightly with Pam; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, mushrooms, onion, oregano, nutmeg, salt and pepper with a wooden spoon.
Beat in eggs. Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture into each of the 18 to 24 muffin cups.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until firm, but still moist. Check often.
Unmold the frittatas and arrange 3 on a plate.
This is also a wonderful side item.
Serves 6.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put the first three ingredients in large covered bowl such as Tupperware. Refrigerate for 3 hours or more. Drain. Heat the sugar and vinegar until dissolved well. Pour over drained pickles. Put in 1 pt. containers and freeze. Makes 6 pints. Will keep well in freezer for up to 3 years.

title: frittata lorraine
directions: Beat together eggs, 3/4 cup cheese, water, bacon, onion, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Melt butter in an iron 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Pour egg mixture in and cook, without stirring, over low to medium heat until set, 7 to 9 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil about 5 to 6 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cool whip delight
directions: Bake flour, butter and pecans in oven 15 minutes until brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Mix 1 package of taco mix with meat.
Add 2 cans mild chili beans to mixture.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Layer in casserole dish:
ground beef mixture, sour cream and sliced cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 300° until hot through and through.
Serve with chips or crackers.
A crowd pleaser.
This makes a large casserole dish full.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn.
Mix beans, corn, sour cream, onion and shredded cheese together in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top of casserole and then pour melted butter over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut rhubarb into small pieces and scatter over crust.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, half and half, flour, salt and vanilla and pour over rhubarb.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, water, oil and salt to a boil.
Cool and pour over drained and chopped vegetables.
Chill overnight in covered bowl.
Stir several times before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: homestyle chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper in a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Stir in vegetables and turkey or chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until mixture bubbles.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix well. Add milk and other ingredients into mixture, one at a time.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine noodles according to package directions.
Have all ingredients ready and close at hand.
Place butter in saut pan and get hot.
Add pasta and toss to warm and coat with butter. Add Parmesan cheese, ham, capers, parsley, salt and pepper, stirring constantly.
Add heavy cream; reduce heat to low.
Stir to combine and let cream reduce to make a nice sauce.
Serve immediately.
You can add chicken or shrimp to this recipe.
The shrimp scampi recipe is a good one to add.
Mushrooms are also good in this recipe.

title: easy candied sweet potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Arrange potatoes in dish. Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool and serve.

title: creme frosting
directions: Gradually add Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 the sugar together. Beat in some skim milk and the vanilla.
Gradually blend in remaining sugar.
Add enough skim milk to make a good spreading consistency.
This is a fat-free frosting.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Divide dough into 12 muffins as evenly as possible.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 12 muffins (2 servings).

title: clam jello(appetizer great for warm weather!)
directions: Follow the instructions for making gelatin, but substitute clam juice for water.
Use less juice than indicated to make a thicker gelatin.
Add a dash of Tabasco to the mix.
Pour the gelatin into a shallow rectangular cake pan.
When it has set, cut into 1 inch cubes.
Arrange lettuce on small salad plates; put about six clam cubes on each plate.
Decorate with dried seeweed shavings.
Serves 6 people.

title: scottish crumpets
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix in flour, salt and and sugar with melted butter and milk to make a smooth batter the consistency of thin cream.
Whisk the egg whites until at the soft peak stage then lightly and quickly fold them into the batter.

Heat a griddle and grease surface lightly, then drop in a large tablespoon at a time, rolling the pan so that the bottom is lightly coated with batter. When golden brown underneath, turn to cook other side.
As crumpets are cooked, roll them in a clean tea towel.
When cool, spread with butter, honey or jam, roll and serve.
Makes about 16.

title: pudding mix
directions: Sift together until well blended; store in a tightly closed container and store on shelf.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Coat a medium size, nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add ham; saute 3 minutes.
Combine ham, flour and next 3 ingredients in a bowl. Add milk, stirring until moistened.
Drop by tablespoons onto baking sheet coated with spray.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes. Yields 1 dozen biscuits.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease and flour large tube cake pan.
Heat oven to 325°. Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until you can insert a toothpick and it comes out clean.
If desired, place semi-sweet chocolate morsels on top as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: layered dinner
directions: Layer in container suitable for oven, 1/2 of hamburger, onion, potatoes, carrots (celery if desired), rest of hamburger and rice. Cover with tomato sauce.
Season, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: Cut fish into serving-size pieces if fish fillets are large. Combine corn meal mixture.
Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Fry fish in hot oil over medium-high heat, turning fish carefully until brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: plum pudding
directions: Soak the first 3 ingredients together for 1 hour.
Combine all ingredients.
Butter a casserole dish.
Bake slowly for about 1 hour at 375°, until knife is clean.

title: lossie's banana nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, shortening, eggs, bananas and sour cream.
Sift soda, flour and salt together.
Add nuts.
Stir in banana mixture. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: celery seed slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper. In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Lightly beat the eggs, melt the margarine and mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strombolia
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add oil, salt and flour.
Knead until smooth; let rise.
Makes two.
Cut dough in half; roll out each half to fit jelly roll pan.
Cover 1/2 of one with pizza sauce.
Put on a layer of ham, each piece covering half of other piece.
Do same with sliced yellow cheese on top of ham.
Add mushrooms and pepperoni and cover with shredded Swiss or Mozzarella cheese.
Bring over uncovered half of dough over ingredients and seal.
Do same with other half of dough.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in 1/2 stick margarine. Crumble 24 crackers plus 2 eggs into 1 pound crab meat.
Add 1 large can evaporated milk, Worcestershire sauce and red hot.
Put all in casserole dish with the vegetables mixed in and top with 24 crumbled crackers in 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: bonnie's salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Mix onions, celery, green pepper and pimentos.
Add oil, sugar and vinegar.
Just add salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Set in the refrigerator overnight.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut margarine into Bisquick.
Add cheese and dill weed; mix well.
Add milk and mix until well blended.
Bake as drop biscuits or in 6 muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until well browned.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spray pan with cooking spray and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: cloud 9
directions: Cream cheese should be room temperature.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts, cherries and pineapple.

title: molasses cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to the molasses.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with remaining dry ingredients.
Blend slightly.
Add melted shortening and beaten egg; beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
I like to bake mine in a 9 x 9-inch iron skillet.
Bake in oven 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, strawberries, sugar, flour, and salt.
Mix well.
Place in 9 inch pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter. Put on top crust.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 400° oven.
Let cool.

title: pizza squares
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage separately.
Drain well and combine. Melt cheese over the meat mixture (microwave).
Spread on each slice of bread and cut in fourths.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to cook.
Place
on cookie sheet and broil until pizza squares brown slightly.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook in a saucepan for 8 minutes, soup, rice and water.
Chop together celery, bell pepper
and onion; saute in butter.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Combine all ingredients (except almonds) and place in casserole.
Add 1/2 cup almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of melted margarine and 2 cups of graham crackers. Mix together and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.
In large bowl, mix 2 cups of confectioners sugar, 1 stick of melted margarine, 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Slice 5 to 6 ripe bananas over mixture.
Drain well 1 large can of crushed pineapple.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with large Cool Whip.
Place cherries and nuts on top.
Sprinkle coconut (optional).

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites. Add sugar and vanilla. Stir in baking powder, crackers and pecans.
Place in pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: marinade for fish
directions: Marinate the fish filets in the combined ingredients and grill fish, onions and peppers.

title: mary's biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening in with a pastry blender or 2 knives until it is the consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk to the flour mixture.
Mix well until it forms a ball (it will be sticky).
On a lightly floured board, roll dough out to about 1/4 inch thick.
Fold the dough in half making 2 layers and cut into rounds.

title: turtle soup
directions: Clean turtle and cut into small pieces.
Boil in salt water until very tender.
Bone and save stock.
Brown flour and onion in oil over low heat.
Mash two hard-boiled egg yolks with cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well and add tomato sauce.
Add tomato mix and boned meat to stock.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add juice or wine, lemon and garlic.
Add egg whites.
Season with salt and pepper. Serves 4.
Preparation Time:
2 hours.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, oatmeal, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda; stir into first mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Slice berries and whip the cream.
Heat water in saucepan. Pour in Jell-O and sugar and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator until thick, but not firm.
Mix in berries, then gently fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking casserole and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and butter or margarine.
Add cocoa, flour and
baking
powder.	When
mixed, pour into 16 x 11-inch pan and bake 45 minutes a 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute celery, pepper, white and green onions in oleo.
Make roux with drippings and flour.
Pour roux and vegetables in big boiler.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp and cook 20 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 10 to 12.
This is much better if made the day before serving.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix well flour and brown sugar.
Add shortening and blend. Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Mix in pan boiling water and both syrups, then add baking soda.
Add liquid mixture to crumb mixture.
Blend and pour through sieve to blend.
Pour batter in pan.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 55 minutes, cupcakes for 35 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Blend dry ingredients together, cut in margarine or butter and continue to blend in lightly.
Mix yogurt and milk together to make 1 cup liquid.
Stir in liquid.
Roll or pat out on a floured board, cut with cookie cutter approximately 2-inches in diameter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet leaving a little space between each scone.
Bake at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a screw-top jar and shake well. Store in the refrigerator.

title: beef chili
directions: In large soup pot, crumble meat in 2-quarts water and cook until meat is done. Add all other ingredients and cook on low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 45 minutes. More water or tomatoes may be added if desired.

title: pecan french toast
directions: Combine eggs, orange juice, milk, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla. Mix with a wire whisk. Place bread in a single layer in a tight fitting casserole. Pour milk mixture over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight, tuning once. Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour melted butter evenly over top. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve with maple syrup and butter. Yield: 4 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved dry yeast.
Combine water and shortening in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
(Shortening does not need to melt.)
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer, scraping bowl occasionally. Add 3/4 cup flour, or enough flour to make a thick batter, eggs and mashed potatoes.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in a large Tupperware greased bowl.

title: 7 quart apple pie mix
directions: Cook mixture until thick and bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients, stirring with a fork until flour is moistened.
Knead 4 to 5 times.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased pan for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush tops with melted margarine.

title: mamie's fudge(million dollar fudge)
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 6 minutes. Put the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is melted and pour into pan. Let stand a few hours before cutting. Store in tin box.

title: amaretto
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Bring sugar and water to a boil, then cool.
When cooled, add coffee mixture, vodka, almond extract, boiling water and vanilla.
Pour into fifths.
Makes 2 fifths.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips and stir-fry in large pan. Add onion. Mix together soups and water. Pour into pan and bring to boil. Add fettucini. Toss and mix well. Serve.

title: bean and cabbage salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Excellent as main dish served with fruit and rolls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all ingredients, except nuts, stand in bowl to soften. Mix and form ball or log shape (best to let mixture set in fridge first to get firm).
Roll ball in nuts and garnish with parsley, if desired.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: colorful bean salad
directions: Peel and divide each tomato in 6 parts and place on 4 plates. Surround with crisp salad greens.
Place bean mixture over tomatoes.

title: boulanger potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes very thin; allow at least one per person. Layer potatoes in greased casserole with onion and cheese alternately.
Pour consomme over all and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
The liquid consomme should nearly cover the contents of the casserole and the casserole should be baked until potatoes are fork-tender.
This is a very extendable recipe.

title: lemon pie(blender lemon pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash lemon.
Leaving peel on, cut into small dice.
Remove seeds and discard.
Place in blender container.
Add eggs, sugar and margarine or butter.
Process well on high speed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and place pie on baking sheet. Bake
40 - 45 minutes, or until set.
Remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: celery seed coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss the shredded cabbage, oil and warm vinegar.
Add the remaining ingredients and toss again.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Spread crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lo-cal smothered baked steak
directions: Brown steak under broiler.
Place in roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over steak.
Roast, uncovered, in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cut meat diagonally.
Serve with pan juices.
Makes 12 servings with 252 calories per serving.

title: bob's caesar salad
directions: Peel, slice garlic lengthwise and place in olive oil overnight. Six hours before dinner, cut bread into cubes of 1/2 to 3/4-inch. You should have at least 4 cups or more.
Place bread on a cookie sheet and dribble with half of the olive oil mixture until all cubes are coated (the rest of the olive oil will be used on the salad).
Bake at 225° for 3 to 4 hours.
After this they should be golden brown.
If not, turn oven to 275° for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: smoked bone soup
directions: Boil first 8 ingredients for one hour.
Remove bones from soup.
Remove meat from bones and put back into soup.
Add rice to soup and cook for 20 minutes.

title: bagels
directions: Combine scalded milk, butter, sugar and salt; let cool somewhat.
Add dissolved yeast and blend in egg(s) and flour. Knead about ten minutes and let rise in greased bowl until double in bulk.
Punch down and divide into 18 pieces.
Let chill until easy to handle, then roll into ropes to form bagel.
Let rise on covered board 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato and berries casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; let cool.
Peel and mash and stir in cranberries and cinnamon.
Spoon into highly greased 2-quart casserole.

title: sausage stars
directions: Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and pepper.
Lightly grease a mini (or regular) muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins, place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In a medium size saucepan, add cooked chicken, vegetables, gravy, soy sauce and pepper to taste. Heat until hot. Serve over hot rice and top with chow mein noodles.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover with frozen onion rings.
(Can use Durkee French fried onions.)
Return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes longer, until onion rings are slightly brown.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, butter and salt.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in soda.
Pour immediately over corn and nuts in large roasting pan.
Bake in slow oven, 250° for one hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in tightly covered container.
Also freezes.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to instructions and cool.
Slice artichoke hearts and onions and add both to rice, including artichoke oil. Add mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: hot cakes or waffles
directions: Slightly beat egg; add milk and sifted dry ingredients alternately.
Add sourdough starter.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted butter and more milk, if you like them thin.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla and nuts or coconut, if desired.
Drop with spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat in skillet, mix in taco mix; drain grease.
Break up lettuce, cut up tomatoes.
Place all ingredients in bowl and mix.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions until tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add other ingredients, except spaghetti, butter and cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Some additional cheese can be sprinkled on top of mixture the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 45 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hamburgers, frankfurters or grilled fish. Makes 4 cups.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine ingredients. Spread over cooled cake. Cut into bars.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Steam raw broccoli or heat frozen broccoli.
Put in blender with 1 soup can water and puree.
Warm cream of chicken soup and broccoli and water mixture until steamy warm.
Add chunks of Velveeta, stirring until melted.
Do not boil!
If you like pieces of broccoli, save out a few pieces for garnish and/or to have "chunky" soup.

title: lime delight
directions: Add jello and boiling water together and stir.
Add cream cheese, cold water and pineapple.
Cool and gel.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill cans 1/2 full.
(I use 4 cans.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take bread out of cans to cool and slip back in cans.
You can put lids on and freeze if you like.
This is good with cream cheese.

title: tex-mex dip(4 layers)
directions: Layer 1:
Spread the bean dip on the bottom of pan.

title: linda's festive corn salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and rinse with water.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour dressing on the top.
Chill 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco; add eggs.
Add sour cream, vanilla and lemon with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: grilled salmon with ginger orange mustard glaze(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Combine first 6 ingredients in a large zip-lock bag.
Add fish to bag, seal and marinate in oven refrigerator for 30+ minutes.

title: ellen honnold's perfect chocolate pie filling
directions: Cocoa Recipe:
In a saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa.
Gradually stir in milk and eggs; cook slowly until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and butter.

title: oatmeal-raisin bars
directions: Spread oats in a shallow pan, and bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan; set aside.

title: angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have ready a tube pan, 10 x 4-inch, but do not grease.
Measure flour by dip-level pour or by sifting.
Sift flour and first amount of sugar together to blend.
Combine egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy.

title: rock candy
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, water, corn syrup and salt. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cover and bring to a rolling boil. Remove lid.
Place candy thermometer in pan and cook to 250°.
Add food coloring and continue cooking to 300°.
Remove from heat at 285° to 290° as temperature will continue rising to 300°.
Let cool a few minutes.
Add flavoring oil and cover 5 more minutes. Pour into a buttered 7 x 10-inch pan.
Cut with shears into strips as soon as cool enough to handle.
Then cut into small pieces and dust with confectioners sugar.
This will keep them from sticking together.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Bake in ungreased pan at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate almond cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream and extracts; mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into a greased 10-in. fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 - 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: reese peanut butter chips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour and baking soda.
In large bowl, beat shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes; cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Add ground beef, salt, oregano, pepper, dry bread crumbs or crackers, tomato sauce, onion and green peppers and stir well.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Combine egg, milk, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, cheese and chili sauce.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Combine tomato sauce (remaining and half of chili sauce).
Heat and serve.

title: party dip for vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients well and serve with a tray of raw, fresh vegetables (carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, celery, etc.).

title: smothered chicken
directions: In a large pot sprayed with Pam, put all chopped vegetables. Cook at medium heat about 2 minutes, stir occasoinally to keep from browning.
Add chicken and 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and cook at medium heat until chicken is done, about 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: mixed vegetable bake
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in small amount of water just until tender.
Drain.
Combine vegetables with water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Combine soup, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, liquid red pepper sauce and cheese.
Mix well.
Toss this mixture with the vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, in 2-quart casserole in a 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with crumbs just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: red punch
directions: Wait until you are ready to drink, then add 1 quart of 7-Up and 1 quart of ice cream (vanilla).

title: yum yogurt drink
directions: Puree all ingredients in blender.
Chill 3 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, celery, and green onion.
Add salt, pepper, and dressing while still hot.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
Before serving add equal amounts of sour cream and mayonnaise.
Chill and serve.

title: norwegian pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, apples, nuts, coconut or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cut in small blocks and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
This recipe gets no shortening.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and drain off excess fat.

title: baked barley
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add barley.
Stir until browned. Add onions, broth and dill.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Bake at 400° until barley is tender and liquid is absorbed (40 minutes). Fluff with a fork to serve.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Be sure they're mixed well. Form into balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: crescent lasagne
directions: Spread 1 can crescent dinner rolls in jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Seal perforations. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Combine cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on baked crescent rolls.
Brown meat and onion; add basil and tomato paste. Place meat mixture on cheese mixture.
Top all with 1 can crescent dinner rolls, arrange triangles to fit.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with Mozzarella.
Turn off oven and return to oven for 3 or 4 more minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed. Roll into small balls and place on baking sheet. Press with fork. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes, until brown. Let cool.

title: very easy cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together.
Make into balls (small or large) depending on size cookies you want.
Roll in powdered sugar and place about 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from cookie sheet to cool on rack.
Cookies should be soft and chewy.
Very good!

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut orange slices, dates and pecans in small pieces; dredge in part of flour.
Pour melted butter over brown sugar and cream. Add eggs one at a time to mixture; beat well after each addition. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla, orange slices and dates and mix well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.
Roll squares in powdered sugar (optional); very good.

title: heavenly smoked brisket
directions: Combine sugar, Cajun seasoning, pepper and Worcestershire in a shallow dish; add brisket, turning to coat both sides.
Cover; chill 8 hours.

title: t.v. nibblers
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 10 x 15-inch pan that is greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.
Turn pan upside down and remove waxed paper before contents cool.
Cut in squares.
Yields about 36 squares.

title: chili con carne with beans
directions: In a large pot, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until liquid evaporates and meat is browned, about 15 minutes. Drain off fat. Stir in seasoning and cook 1 minute. Add tomatoes with their liquid and water and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or more, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans, olives, mushrooms and salt. Serve with chopped green onion and shredded low-fat cheese.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line a large baking dish with pie crust, with enough left for a top on cobbler.
Prick crust.
Pour peaches with juice and sugar in crust, mix gently.
Crush crackers not real fine, add to peaches.
Cut butter into small pieces; add to peaches.
Leave this juicy.
Top with crust and dot with more butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Heat 3 cups milk and chicken base slowly over low heat until hot.
In a separate bowl, mix together 1 cup milk, corn starch and white pepper.
Slowly add corn starch mixture to saucepan and bring just to boiling.
Stirring constantly, simmer gently for an additional 2-3 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: To slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk and spices. Cook until thick in double boiler. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water and add to hot pumpkin mixture. Mix thoroughly and let cool. Beat egg whites with remaining 1/2 cup sugar and fold into cool pumpkin mixture. Pour into baked pie shell. Chill before serving. Makes 1 pie.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil and mix at medium speed until there is no visible trace of oil (at least 3 minutes).
Add flour, soda, salt and spice.
Mix until blended, then add pumpkin mix at low speed until well blended.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in preheated 350°
oven for 1 hour.
Delicious with cream cheese icing.

title: apple chicken saute
directions: Remove skin from chicken; cut into 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch strips. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Saute chicken until cooked; remove from pan.
Add oil to skillet, if necessary.
Saute green pepper and onion until crisp-tender.
Return chicken to vegetables.
Add apple and heat thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to apple mixture and cook until sauce thickens. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: mexican beef and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or boil for 2 minutes and let soak 1 hour.
Brown meat well
on
all
sides.
Saute
onions until limp and
lightly
browned.
Add garlic, salt, chillies, cumin and chili powder.
Return
meat
to pan.
Add beans, including the liquid.
Cover
and
simmer
slowly until beans are almost tender, about 2
hours,
adding
water if needed to keep beans covered. Add tomato
sauce
and
cook until beans are tender, about 1 hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice; set aside.
Brown pork in oil in large pan; stir in water.
Cover and simmer while preparing other ingredients.
Combine sugar, starch and salt in bowl.
Stir in pineapple juice and vinegar mixture into pork.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Heat chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks slightly; stir with vanilla into melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in 2 1/2 qt. bowl until foamy. Beat in sugar, 1 tbsp. at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Stir about 1/4 of the meringue into chocolate mixture.
Fold into remaining meringue.
Beat whipping cream in chilled small bowl until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture. Spoon into dessert dish.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Top each serving with additional sweetened whipped cream and grated chocolate if desired.

title: virginia chunk sweet pickles
directions: Make brine of a proportion of 2 cups salt to 1 gallon water. Boil and pour over pickles boiling hot.
Let stand one week.

title: butter toffee
directions: For Microwave:
In large 2 to 3-quart Pyrex mixing bowl, rub top of bowl with stick of butter.
Put remaining butter in bottom of bowl and carefully pour the sugar-salt mixture on the butter. Pour water on top.
Microwave 8 minutes.
It will not be done at this time.
Add additional time in 30 second increments.
You must open the door of oven every 30 seconds and look in.
The candy is done when it turns caramel brown color.
Never stir this candy. Place foil on cookie sheet.
Top with nuts and pour candy over nuts.
Have the foil and nuts ready before you start your 8 minutes in the microwave.
Don't scrape the bowl!
Set at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate for 1 1/2 minutes and pour over toffee.
Chill and break into pieces.

title: quick picante dip
directions: Heat together and have lots of chips.

title: tuna fish pie with cheese roll crust
directions: Melt butter. Add pepper and onion; cook until soft.
Add flour. Stir until well blended. Add salt and milk slowly.
Stir constantly until thick and smooth.
Bring to a boil 2 minutes. Add tuna and lemon juice.
Pour into
a large baking dish and cover with Cheese Rolls.

title: pink surprise ice cream
directions: Mash bananas and begin to add all the other ingredients.
Then put in can and freeze.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add onion, garlic salt/powder, catsup, vinegar, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add bacon and beans, undrained.
